{"type":"message","id":"3b40519f","parentId":"559be416","timestamp":"2026-04-12T03:57:44.099Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_am2rlkgcbf6p_1","toolName":"sessions_list","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"count\": 8,\n  \"sessions\": [\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"telegram\",\n      \"origin\": {\n        \"provider\": \"telegram\",\n        \"accountId\": \"main_bot\"\n      },\n      \"displayName\": \"Khương Nịnh (@khuowgn) id:6053576134\",\n      \"deliveryContext\": {\n        \"channel\": \"telegram\",\n        \"to\": \"telegram:6053576134\",\n        \"accountId\": \"main_bot\"\n      },\n      \"updatedAt\": 1775966254803,\n      \"sessionId\": \"7ae3b683-0b91-4427-abbe-b78ef94eb140\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 200000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 113381,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"done\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1775966230424,\n      \"endedAt\": 1775966253722,\n      \"runtimeMs\": 23298,\n      \"systemSent\": true,\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"lastChannel\": \"telegram\",\n      \"lastTo\": \"telegram:6053576134\",\n      \"lastAccountId\": \"main_bot\",\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/7ae3b683-0b91-4427-abbe-b78ef94eb140.jsonl\",\n      \"messages\": [\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"thinking\",\n              \"thinking\": \"Now I understand the full picture. The user wants:\\n\\n1. When a task is assigned to an agent → a message should go into the group\\n2. When an agent completes work → a message should go into the group\\n3. When there are changes/updates → a message should go into the group\\n\\nCurrently, the flow is working through master-orchestrator (tuowgn) as the coordinator, but the user wants each agent to be able to report directly into the group.\\n\\nLooking at the conversation, it seems the user wants **Option A** - each agent reports directly into the group. But they're also seeing that `master-orchestrator` (tuowgn) is the one currently reporting. \\n\\nThe core issue is that only the master orchestrator bot is posting in the group, while the other agents are completing their work silently. To fix this, I need to figure out how to get each agent to post their status directly to Telegram rather than just completing their tasks in the background. I'm realizing the core issue: if each agent should report directly to the group, they need their own Telegram bot accounts to send messages independently. The current setup only has master-orchestrator able to post. So either each of the 34 agents needs a dedicated bot (which requires 34 BotFather tokens), or we route everything through master-orchestrator as a single spokesperson. Given the architecture constraints, the user's requirement probably means each agent should announce itself when taking a task and when completing it, rather than posting detailed work. So the real issue is that while the orchestrator can receive results from sub-agents, those agents can't directly post back to the group—they can only send messages to the user who initiated them, not to arbitrary Telegram groups. To enable direct group posting from sub-agents, I'd need to add group chat permissions to their accounts, but the cleanest solution for the user's need is probably to have the orchestrator handle group communication on behalf of all agents, collecting their outputs and posting summaries to the group. I'm considering whether to suggest the user create new Telegram bots for the specialist agents they want reporting directly, or if there's a simpler workaround where agents can send messages to the group without needing separate bot accounts for each one.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \" Mình hiểu rõ rồi. Hiện tại bạn chỉ thấy `master-orchestrator` nhắn vì:\\n\\n- sub-agent **chỉ reply về cho master** chứ **không tự gửi message vào group được**\\n- muốn mỗi agent nhắn thẳng vào group → cần **mỗi agent có bot Telegram riêng** để gửi message\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Vậy câu hỏi để xác định hướng đúng:\\n\\n### Bạn muốn mỗi agent có identity Telegram riêng không?\\nTức là khi `ui-design-system` nhắn, bạn muốn thấy:\\n- **icon tên riêng** của `ui-design-system_bot`\\n- message hiển thị dưới tên `@ui_design_system_bot`\\n- không phải chung 1 tên `master-orchestrator`\\n\\n### Nếu **CÓ** — muốn mỗi agent nhắn riêng\\n→ Cần **tạo thêm bot Telegram accounts** cho các agent cần gửi message vào group. Mỗi bot cần:\\n1. tạo qua @BotFather\\n2. lấy token\\n3. thêm vào `channels.telegram.accounts` trong `openclaw.json`\\n4. agent gọi `sessions_send` hoặc dùng tool message gửi qua account đó\\n\\n### Nếu **KHÔNG** — chỉ cần master-orchestrator làm spokesperson\\n→ Mình sẽ lập trình sẵn trong `master-orchestrator`:\\n- mỗi khi nhận task → báo vào group\\n- mỗi khi agent báo về → tổng hợp → báo vào group\\n- group chỉ thấy 1 nguồn duy nhất từ master\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Trả lời tôi đúng 1 câu:\\n- **\\\"mỗi agent nhắn riêng\\\"** → mình sẽ hướng dẫn bạn tạo thêm Telegram bot accounts cho các agent\\n- **\\\"chỉ master nhắn thôi\\\"** → mình sẽ lập trình sẵn cơ chế báo cáo tự động trong master-orchestrator\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n          \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 0,\n            \"output\": 1042,\n            \"totalTokens\": 114423,\n            \"cacheRead\": 109623,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 3758,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1775966230432,\n          \"responseId\": \"062a4b1830fca2b4718aab6c4aea80e1\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"308cea21\",\n            \"seq\": 261\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:stitch-design:main\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"unknown\",\n      \"updatedAt\": 1775965969105,\n      \"sessionId\": \"8232fb03-6e1d-4e59-9170-ded1fd82e68f\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 200000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 32819,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"running\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1775965969065,\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"/root/.openclaw/agents/stitch-design/sessions/8232fb03-6e1d-4e59-9170-ded1fd82e68f.jsonl\",\n      \"messages\": []\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:ui-design-system:main\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"unknown\",\n      \"updatedAt\": 1775965906153,\n      \"sessionId\": \"aa862f9c-22aa-4dd7-baa2-fdd1c0b705e8\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-TroLy\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 200000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 22926,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"failed\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1775965627842,\n      \"endedAt\": 1775965891137,\n      \"runtimeMs\": 263295,\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"/root/.openclaw/agents/ui-design-system/sessions/aa862f9c-22aa-4dd7-baa2-fdd1c0b705e8.jsonl\",\n      \"messages\": []\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:ui-ux-pro-max:subagent:d533555e-8a84-4f30-a0a1-a2bc93b09026\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"telegram\",\n      \"spawnedBy\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5212380728\",\n      \"label\": \"luxury-ecom:ui-ux-pro-max\",\n      \"displayName\": \"telegram:g-agent-ui-ux-pro-max-subagent-d533555e-8a84-4f30-a0a1-a2bc93b09026\",\n      \"parentSessionKey\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5212380728\",\n      \"deliveryContext\": {\n        \"channel\": \"telegram\"\n      },\n      \"updatedAt\": 1775965666810,\n      \"sessionId\": \"d29502b2-d96e-4109-9756-87d40880ec0b\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-TroLy\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 200000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 47241,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"done\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1775965206375,\n      \"endedAt\": 1775965657795,\n      \"runtimeMs\": 432789,\n      \"thinkingLevel\": \"medium\",\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"lastChannel\": \"telegram\",\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"/root/.openclaw/agents/ui-ux-pro-max/sessions/d29502b2-d96e-4109-9756-87d40880ec0b.jsonl\",\n      \"messages\": [\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"Completed:\\n- Read and applied the `ui-ux-pro-max` skill.\\n- Produced a full UX direction document for the luxury e-commerce app.\\n- Wrote it to:\\n  - `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/HANDOVER.md`\\n- Dispatched downstream agent turns:\\n  - `ui-design-system` with the HANDOVER content\\n  - `stitch-design` with the full Stitch generation brief for `projects/12108154905534221530`\\n\\nKey contents in the handover:\\n- Browse → discover → decide → purchase → track flows\\n- Mobile-first IA and nav hierarchy\\n- Interaction rules: 44x44 targets, gestures, loading/feedback states\\n- Luxury motion guidelines\\n- Luxury-specific UX principles\\n- Screen-by-screen intent and downstream instructions\\n\\nRelevant note:\\n- The workspace protocol required `prompt-optimizer` first; I initiated that agent turn as well, but it was still waiting on reply when I completed the requested deliverables and downstream dispatches.\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n          \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-TroLy\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 2185,\n            \"output\": 217,\n            \"totalTokens\": 47458,\n            \"cacheRead\": 45056,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 0,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1775965633117,\n          \"responseId\": \"1775965634449\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"5c86bbf5\",\n            \"seq\": 28\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:prompt-optimizer:main\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"unknown\",\n      \"updatedAt\": 1775965481997,\n      \"sessionId\": \"2c50e4c8-6c71-45da-8c3f-4e76697147e7\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-TroLy\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 200000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 15966,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"done\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1775965397801,\n      \"endedAt\": 1775965481635,\n      \"runtimeMs\": 83834,\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"/root/.openclaw/agents/prompt-optimizer/sessions/2c50e4c8-6c71-45da-8c3f-4e76697147e7.jsonl\",\n      \"messages\": [\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \" **Section 1: Prompt Diagnosis**\\n\\n**Strengths:** Strong brand direction, clear screen/component scope, defined palette/typography/motion, and explicit UX tasks.\\n\\n**Issues:**\\n\\n| Issue | Impact | Suggested Fix |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| No primary business goal stated | Agents may optimize for aesthetics over conversion | Add measurable UX/commercial objectives |\\n| Audience is broad | Luxury positioning may become generic | Specify expectations for affluent, high-intent shoppers |\\n| Priorities are not ranked | Agents may overinvest in low-value screens | State must-have vs secondary outputs |\\n| Constraints are incomplete | Outputs may drift into non-luxury patterns | Add accessibility, mobile-first, restraint, and no-discount-noise rules |\\n| Deliverables are implied, not explicit | Downstream outputs may be inconsistent | Define exact artifacts required |\\n\\n**Needs Clarification:**\\n1. Should the experience emphasize brand discovery/editorial storytelling equally with conversion, or conversion first?\\n2. Are promotions/discount-first patterns intentionally excluded to preserve luxury positioning?\\n3. Should agents produce wire-level UX guidance only, or also content direction/microcopy tone?\\n\\n---\\n\\n**Section 2: Recommended Components**\\n\\n| Type | Component | Purpose |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| Skill | `@prompt-optimizer` | Refines the brief into a copy-paste downstream agent prompt |\\n| Skill | `@ui-design-system` | Interprets visual system, component hierarchy, and luxury UI direction |\\n| Skill | `@senior-architect` | Structures IA, flows, and interaction system coherently |\\n| Skill | `@master-orchestrator` | Useful if multiple design agents will split screens, flows, and system guidance |\\n\\n---\\n\\n**Section 3: Optimized Prompt — Full Version**\\n\\n```text\\nCreate a concise UX direction brief for downstream design agents for a mobile-first premium luxury e-commerce app.\\n\\nContext\\n- App type: premium luxury e-commerce\\n- Target users: affluent men and women with high purchase intent, strong brand sensitivity, and expectation of polish, trust, and exclusivity\\n- Brand attributes: premium, minimal, editorial, exclusive, timeless\\n- Visual tone: quiet luxury, not flashy; refined, restrained, and high-end\\n\\nDesign foundations\\n- Primary color: black #0B0B0C\\n- Support palette:\\n  - soft gold #C6A972\\n  - ivory #F6F1E8\\n  - warm white #FAF8F4\\n  - charcoal #1A1A1D\\n  - muted gray #8C8C8F\\n- Typography:\\n  - headings: elegant serif\\n  - body/UI: modern sans-serif\\n- Motion:\\n  - soft, restrained, luxurious\\n  - use fade-ins, gentle hover lifts, smooth transitions\\n  - avoid energetic, playful, or attention-seeking animation\\n\\nScreen scope\\n- Home\\n- Collection / Category Listing\\n- Search\\n- Product Detail\\n- Wishlist\\n- Cart\\n- Checkout\\n- Sign In\\n- Sign Up\\n- Forgot Password\\n- Profile / Account\\n- Order History\\n- Order Detail\\n- Featured Collection Landing\\n- Editorial Campaign Page\\n\\nComponent scope\\n- Navigation\\n- Hero banners\\n- Category cards\\n- Product tiles\\n- Filters and sort\\n- Buttons\\n- Form inputs\\n- Badges / labels\\n- Empty states\\n- Checkout sections\\n- Order summaries\\n- Wishlist\\n- Cart\\n- Footer\\n- Editorial panels\\n\\nPrimary objectives\\n1. Deliver a luxury-first browsing and shopping experience that feels exclusive, calm, and premium.\\n2. Balance editorial brand storytelling with frictionless commerce.\\n3. Help users move confidently from browse → discover → decide → purchase → track.\\n4. Increase clarity, trust, and purchase intent without visual clutter.\\n\\nUX priorities\\n1. Mobile-first clarity and elegance\\n2. Premium perception through restraint, spacing, hierarchy, and imagery treatment\\n3. Fast product discovery and confident product evaluation\\n4. Seamless checkout with minimal friction\\n5. Strong account and order-tracking usability\\n6. Consistent luxury tone across utility screens, not just marketing pages\\n\\nConstraints\\n- Mobile-first; prioritize handheld interactions before larger breakpoints\\n- Maintain a minimal editorial aesthetic across all screens\\n- Avoid discount-heavy, noisy, mass-market e-commerce patterns\\n- Preserve strong readability and accessibility\\n- Use touch targets of at least 44px\\n- Keep navigation simple, predictable, and unobtrusive\\n- Motion must support polish, not spectacle\\n- Favor whitespace, typography, and image-led hierarchy over dense UI chrome\\n\\nRequired outputs\\nProduce a clarified UX brief with these sections:\\n\\n1. Objectives\\n- Summarize the experience goals in 4–6 bullets\\n\\n2. Experience principles for luxury commerce\\n- Define 5–7 UX principles tailored to luxury retail\\n- Examples: restraint, confidence, trust, editorial hierarchy, premium pacing, tactile clarity\\n\\n3. User flow map\\n- Define the end-to-end flow: browse → discover → decide → purchase → track\\n- Include key decision points, friction risks, and moments where luxury perception must be preserved\\n\\n4. Information architecture and navigation hierarchy\\n- Define top-level navigation, secondary navigation, account/order areas, and cross-links between editorial and commerce\\n- Clarify how users move between Home, Collection, Search, PDP, Wishlist, Cart, Checkout, and Account\\n\\n5. Interaction patterns\\n- Define:\\n  - tap target minimums\\n  - gesture usage\\n  - filter/sort behavior\\n  - search behavior\\n  - wishlist/cart interactions\\n  - form behavior\\n  - validation and error handling\\n  - loading, empty, and success states\\n- Keep patterns premium, calm, and predictable\\n\\n6. Motion guidelines\\n- Specify animation principles, timing feel, where motion is appropriate, and where it should be avoided\\n- Keep motion subtle and luxurious\\n\\n7. Screen and component priorities\\n- Rank which screens/components require the highest UX fidelity first\\n- Identify must-have patterns vs secondary enhancements\\n\\n8. Deliverables for downstream design agents\\n- Provide explicit deliverables:\\n  - UX brief\\n  - flow map\\n  - IA/navigation hierarchy\\n  - interaction pattern guidelines\\n  - motion guidelines\\n  - prioritized screen list\\n  - component behavior notes\\n\\nOutput requirements\\n- Be concise, structured, and ready for design execution\\n- Use clear headings and bullets\\n- Optimize for downstream design agents, not stakeholders\\n- Do not write implementation code\\n- Do not expand scope beyond the listed screens/components\\n- Do not introduce playful, trend-driven, or mass-market retail patterns\\n```\\n\\nIf you want, I can also compress this into a **shorter “agent-ready brief” version** of ~150–220 words.\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n          \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-TroLy\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 13406,\n            \"output\": 1505,\n            \"totalTokens\": 17471,\n            \"cacheRead\": 2560,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 0,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1775965405625,\n          \"responseId\": \"1775965408885\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"6f8e5def\",\n            \"seq\": 4\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:ui-ux-pro-max:subagent:9cc5ade0-1d6d-4cc0-8232-5450257406d3\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"telegram\",\n      \"spawnedBy\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5212380728\",\n      \"label\": \"luxury-ecom:ui-ux-pro-max\",\n      \"displayName\": \"telegram:g-agent-ui-ux-pro-max-subagent-9cc5ade0-1d6d-4cc0-8232-5450257406d3\",\n      \"parentSessionKey\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5212380728\",\n      \"deliveryContext\": {\n        \"channel\": \"telegram\"\n      },\n      \"updatedAt\": 1775965120525,\n      \"sessionId\": \"c22a2990-48e8-47c2-bbe6-3aa7c11f6d1c\",\n      \"model\": \"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 200000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 10326,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"failed\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1775965047235,\n      \"endedAt\": 1775965092883,\n      \"runtimeMs\": 0,\n      \"thinkingLevel\": \"medium\",\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"lastChannel\": \"telegram\",\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"/root/.openclaw/agents/ui-ux-pro-max/sessions/c22a2990-48e8-47c2-bbe6-3aa7c11f6d1c.jsonl\",\n      \"messages\": []\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:prompt-optimizer:subagent:9a0bd8d6-856e-4e24-ad1f-007e2908253d\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"telegram\",\n      \"spawnedBy\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5212380728\",\n      \"label\": \"luxury-ecom:prompt-optimizer\",\n      \"displayName\": \"telegram:g-maiychrus25-company-.ltd\",\n      \"parentSessionKey\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5212380728\",\n      \"deliveryContext\": {\n        \"channel\": \"telegram\"\n      },\n      \"updatedAt\": 1775965054667,\n      \"sessionId\": \"29634186-b281-45ea-b6f7-20b75e2416c3\",\n      \"model\": \"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 200000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 10128,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"failed\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1775964888321,\n      \"endedAt\": 1775965026708,\n      \"runtimeMs\": 64902,\n      \"thinkingLevel\": \"medium\",\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"lastChannel\": \"telegram\",\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"/root/.openclaw/agents/prompt-optimizer/sessions/29634186-b281-45ea-b6f7-20b75e2416c3.jsonl\",\n      \"messages\": []\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:main\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"heartbeat\",\n      \"origin\": {\n        \"provider\": \"heartbeat\"\n      },\n      \"displayName\": \"heartbeat\",\n      \"deliveryContext\": {\n        \"to\": \"heartbeat\"\n      },\n      \"updatedAt\": 1775964997833,\n      \"sessionId\": \"e2d6305b-be5b-4582-92f2-b0085b69bc13\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-TroLy\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 200000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 60555,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"done\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1775964963469,\n      \"endedAt\": 1775964997469,\n      \"runtimeMs\": 34000,\n      \"systemSent\": true,\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"lastTo\": \"heartbeat\",\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/e2d6305b-be5b-4582-92f2-b0085b69bc13.jsonl\",\n      \"messages\": [\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"🌐 AGENT PRESENCE BOARD — 10:35 UTC+7\\n\\n╔═══════════════════════════════════════╗\\n║ 🟡 prompt-optimizer   running         ║\\n║ 🟢 master-orchestrator recent done    ║\\n║ ⚪ other agents        standby         ║\\n╠═══════════════════════════════════════╣\\n║ Total: 1 active / 34 agents          ║\\n╚═══════════════════════════════════════╝\\n\\nPipeline: HEALTHY ✅\\nAlerts: none\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n          \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-TroLy\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 7563,\n            \"output\": 323,\n            \"totalTokens\": 60878,\n            \"cacheRead\": 52992,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 0,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1775964976755,\n          \"responseId\": \"1775964979413\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"16846598\",\n            \"seq\": 96\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"count":8,"sessions":[{"key":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134","kind":"other","channel":"telegram","origin":{"provider":"telegram","accountId":"main_bot"},"displayName":"Khương Nịnh (@khuowgn) id:6053576134","deliveryContext":{"channel":"telegram","to":"telegram:6053576134","accountId":"main_bot"},"updatedAt":1775966254803,"sessionId":"7ae3b683-0b91-4427-abbe-b78ef94eb140","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":113381,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"done","startedAt":1775966230424,"endedAt":1775966253722,"runtimeMs":23298,"systemSent":true,"abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"telegram","lastTo":"telegram:6053576134","lastAccountId":"main_bot","transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/7ae3b683-0b91-4427-abbe-b78ef94eb140.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture. The user wants:\n\n1. When a task is assigned to an agent → a message should go into the group\n2. When an agent completes work → a message should go into the group\n3. When there are changes/updates → a message should go into the group\n\nCurrently, the flow is working through master-orchestrator (tuowgn) as the coordinator, but the user wants each agent to be able to report directly into the group.\n\nLooking at the conversation, it seems the user wants **Option A** - each agent reports directly into the group. But they're also seeing that `master-orchestrator` (tuowgn) is the one currently reporting. \n\nThe core issue is that only the master orchestrator bot is posting in the group, while the other agents are completing their work silently. To fix this, I need to figure out how to get each agent to post their status directly to Telegram rather than just completing their tasks in the background. I'm realizing the core issue: if each agent should report directly to the group, they need their own Telegram bot accounts to send messages independently. The current setup only has master-orchestrator able to post. So either each of the 34 agents needs a dedicated bot (which requires 34 BotFather tokens), or we route everything through master-orchestrator as a single spokesperson. Given the architecture constraints, the user's requirement probably means each agent should announce itself when taking a task and when completing it, rather than posting detailed work. So the real issue is that while the orchestrator can receive results from sub-agents, those agents can't directly post back to the group—they can only send messages to the user who initiated them, not to arbitrary Telegram groups. To enable direct group posting from sub-agents, I'd need to add group chat permissions to their accounts, but the cleanest solution for the user's need is probably to have the orchestrator handle group communication on behalf of all agents, collecting their outputs and posting summaries to the group. I'm considering whether to suggest the user create new Telegram bots for the specialist agents they want reporting directly, or if there's a simpler workaround where agents can send messages to the group without needing separate bot accounts for each one."},{"type":"text","text":" Mình hiểu rõ rồi. Hiện tại bạn chỉ thấy `master-orchestrator` nhắn vì:\n\n- sub-agent **chỉ reply về cho master** chứ **không tự gửi message vào group được**\n- muốn mỗi agent nhắn thẳng vào group → cần **mỗi agent có bot Telegram riêng** để gửi message\n\n---\n\n## Vậy câu hỏi để xác định hướng đúng:\n\n### Bạn muốn mỗi agent có identity Telegram riêng không?\nTức là khi `ui-design-system` nhắn, bạn muốn thấy:\n- **icon tên riêng** của `ui-design-system_bot`\n- message hiển thị dưới tên `@ui_design_system_bot`\n- không phải chung 1 tên `master-orchestrator`\n\n### Nếu **CÓ** — muốn mỗi agent nhắn riêng\n→ Cần **tạo thêm bot Telegram accounts** cho các agent cần gửi message vào group. Mỗi bot cần:\n1. tạo qua @BotFather\n2. lấy token\n3. thêm vào `channels.telegram.accounts` trong `openclaw.json`\n4. agent gọi `sessions_send` hoặc dùng tool message gửi qua account đó\n\n### Nếu **KHÔNG** — chỉ cần master-orchestrator làm spokesperson\n→ Mình sẽ lập trình sẵn trong `master-orchestrator`:\n- mỗi khi nhận task → báo vào group\n- mỗi khi agent báo về → tổng hợp → báo vào group\n- group chỉ thấy 1 nguồn duy nhất từ master\n\n---\n\n## Trả lời tôi đúng 1 câu:\n- **\"mỗi agent nhắn riêng\"** → mình sẽ hướng dẫn bạn tạo thêm Telegram bot accounts cho các agent\n- **\"chỉ master nhắn thôi\"** → mình sẽ lập trình sẵn cơ chế báo cáo tự động trong master-orchestrator"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":0,"output":1042,"totalTokens":114423,"cacheRead":109623,"cacheWrite":3758,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775966230432,"responseId":"062a4b1830fca2b4718aab6c4aea80e1","__openclaw":{"id":"308cea21","seq":261}}]},{"key":"agent:stitch-design:main","kind":"other","channel":"unknown","updatedAt":1775965969105,"sessionId":"8232fb03-6e1d-4e59-9170-ded1fd82e68f","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":32819,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"running","startedAt":1775965969065,"abortedLastRun":false,"transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/stitch-design/sessions/8232fb03-6e1d-4e59-9170-ded1fd82e68f.jsonl","messages":[]},{"key":"agent:ui-design-system:main","kind":"other","channel":"unknown","updatedAt":1775965906153,"sessionId":"aa862f9c-22aa-4dd7-baa2-fdd1c0b705e8","model":"AHV-Holding-TroLy","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":22926,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"failed","startedAt":1775965627842,"endedAt":1775965891137,"runtimeMs":263295,"abortedLastRun":false,"transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/ui-design-system/sessions/aa862f9c-22aa-4dd7-baa2-fdd1c0b705e8.jsonl","messages":[]},{"key":"agent:ui-ux-pro-max:subagent:d533555e-8a84-4f30-a0a1-a2bc93b09026","kind":"other","channel":"telegram","spawnedBy":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5212380728","label":"luxury-ecom:ui-ux-pro-max","displayName":"telegram:g-agent-ui-ux-pro-max-subagent-d533555e-8a84-4f30-a0a1-a2bc93b09026","parentSessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5212380728","deliveryContext":{"channel":"telegram"},"updatedAt":1775965666810,"sessionId":"d29502b2-d96e-4109-9756-87d40880ec0b","model":"AHV-Holding-TroLy","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":47241,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"done","startedAt":1775965206375,"endedAt":1775965657795,"runtimeMs":432789,"thinkingLevel":"medium","abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"telegram","transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/ui-ux-pro-max/sessions/d29502b2-d96e-4109-9756-87d40880ec0b.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Completed:\n- Read and applied the `ui-ux-pro-max` skill.\n- Produced a full UX direction document for the luxury e-commerce app.\n- Wrote it to:\n  - `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/HANDOVER.md`\n- Dispatched downstream agent turns:\n  - `ui-design-system` with the HANDOVER content\n  - `stitch-design` with the full Stitch generation brief for `projects/12108154905534221530`\n\nKey contents in the handover:\n- Browse → discover → decide → purchase → track flows\n- Mobile-first IA and nav hierarchy\n- Interaction rules: 44x44 targets, gestures, loading/feedback states\n- Luxury motion guidelines\n- Luxury-specific UX principles\n- Screen-by-screen intent and downstream instructions\n\nRelevant note:\n- The workspace protocol required `prompt-optimizer` first; I initiated that agent turn as well, but it was still waiting on reply when I completed the requested deliverables and downstream dispatches."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-TroLy","usage":{"input":2185,"output":217,"totalTokens":47458,"cacheRead":45056,"cacheWrite":0,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775965633117,"responseId":"1775965634449","__openclaw":{"id":"5c86bbf5","seq":28}}]},{"key":"agent:prompt-optimizer:main","kind":"other","channel":"unknown","updatedAt":1775965481997,"sessionId":"2c50e4c8-6c71-45da-8c3f-4e76697147e7","model":"AHV-Holding-TroLy","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":15966,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"done","startedAt":1775965397801,"endedAt":1775965481635,"runtimeMs":83834,"abortedLastRun":false,"transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/prompt-optimizer/sessions/2c50e4c8-6c71-45da-8c3f-4e76697147e7.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":" **Section 1: Prompt Diagnosis**\n\n**Strengths:** Strong brand direction, clear screen/component scope, defined palette/typography/motion, and explicit UX tasks.\n\n**Issues:**\n\n| Issue | Impact | Suggested Fix |\n|---|---|---|\n| No primary business goal stated | Agents may optimize for aesthetics over conversion | Add measurable UX/commercial objectives |\n| Audience is broad | Luxury positioning may become generic | Specify expectations for affluent, high-intent shoppers |\n| Priorities are not ranked | Agents may overinvest in low-value screens | State must-have vs secondary outputs |\n| Constraints are incomplete | Outputs may drift into non-luxury patterns | Add accessibility, mobile-first, restraint, and no-discount-noise rules |\n| Deliverables are implied, not explicit | Downstream outputs may be inconsistent | Define exact artifacts required |\n\n**Needs Clarification:**\n1. Should the experience emphasize brand discovery/editorial storytelling equally with conversion, or conversion first?\n2. Are promotions/discount-first patterns intentionally excluded to preserve luxury positioning?\n3. Should agents produce wire-level UX guidance only, or also content direction/microcopy tone?\n\n---\n\n**Section 2: Recommended Components**\n\n| Type | Component | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| Skill | `@prompt-optimizer` | Refines the brief into a copy-paste downstream agent prompt |\n| Skill | `@ui-design-system` | Interprets visual system, component hierarchy, and luxury UI direction |\n| Skill | `@senior-architect` | Structures IA, flows, and interaction system coherently |\n| Skill | `@master-orchestrator` | Useful if multiple design agents will split screens, flows, and system guidance |\n\n---\n\n**Section 3: Optimized Prompt — Full Version**\n\n```text\nCreate a concise UX direction brief for downstream design agents for a mobile-first premium luxury e-commerce app.\n\nContext\n- App type: premium luxury e-commerce\n- Target users: affluent men and women with high purchase intent, strong brand sensitivity, and expectation of polish, trust, and exclusivity\n- Brand attributes: premium, minimal, editorial, exclusive, timeless\n- Visual tone: quiet luxury, not flashy; refined, restrained, and high-end\n\nDesign foundations\n- Primary color: black #0B0B0C\n- Support palette:\n  - soft gold #C6A972\n  - ivory #F6F1E8\n  - warm white #FAF8F4\n  - charcoal #1A1A1D\n  - muted gray #8C8C8F\n- Typography:\n  - headings: elegant serif\n  - body/UI: modern sans-serif\n- Motion:\n  - soft, restrained, luxurious\n  - use fade-ins, gentle hover lifts, smooth transitions\n  - avoid energetic, playful, or attention-seeking animation\n\nScreen scope\n- Home\n- Collection / Category Listing\n- Search\n- Product Detail\n- Wishlist\n- Cart\n- Checkout\n- Sign In\n- Sign Up\n- Forgot Password\n- Profile / Account\n- Order History\n- Order Detail\n- Featured Collection Landing\n- Editorial Campaign Page\n\nComponent scope\n- Navigation\n- Hero banners\n- Category cards\n- Product tiles\n- Filters and sort\n- Buttons\n- Form inputs\n- Badges / labels\n- Empty states\n- Checkout sections\n- Order summaries\n- Wishlist\n- Cart\n- Footer\n- Editorial panels\n\nPrimary objectives\n1. Deliver a luxury-first browsing and shopping experience that feels exclusive, calm, and premium.\n2. Balance editorial brand storytelling with frictionless commerce.\n3. Help users move confidently from browse → discover → decide → purchase → track.\n4. Increase clarity, trust, and purchase intent without visual clutter.\n\nUX priorities\n1. Mobile-first clarity and elegance\n2. Premium perception through restraint, spacing, hierarchy, and imagery treatment\n3. Fast product discovery and confident product evaluation\n4. Seamless checkout with minimal friction\n5. Strong account and order-tracking usability\n6. Consistent luxury tone across utility screens, not just marketing pages\n\nConstraints\n- Mobile-first; prioritize handheld interactions before larger breakpoints\n- Maintain a minimal editorial aesthetic across all screens\n- Avoid discount-heavy, noisy, mass-market e-commerce patterns\n- Preserve strong readability and accessibility\n- Use touch targets of at least 44px\n- Keep navigation simple, predictable, and unobtrusive\n- Motion must support polish, not spectacle\n- Favor whitespace, typography, and image-led hierarchy over dense UI chrome\n\nRequired outputs\nProduce a clarified UX brief with these sections:\n\n1. Objectives\n- Summarize the experience goals in 4–6 bullets\n\n2. Experience principles for luxury commerce\n- Define 5–7 UX principles tailored to luxury retail\n- Examples: restraint, confidence, trust, editorial hierarchy, premium pacing, tactile clarity\n\n3. User flow map\n- Define the end-to-end flow: browse → discover → decide → purchase → track\n- Include key decision points, friction risks, and moments where luxury perception must be preserved\n\n4. Information architecture and navigation hierarchy\n- Define top-level navigation, secondary navigation, account/order areas, and cross-links between editorial and commerce\n- Clarify how users move between Home, Collection, Search, PDP, Wishlist, Cart, Checkout, and Account\n\n5. Interaction patterns\n- Define:\n  - tap target minimums\n  - gesture usage\n  - filter/sort behavior\n  - search behavior\n  - wishlist/cart interactions\n  - form behavior\n  - validation and error handling\n  - loading, empty, and success states\n- Keep patterns premium, calm, and predictable\n\n6. Motion guidelines\n- Specify animation principles, timing feel, where motion is appropriate, and where it should be avoided\n- Keep motion subtle and luxurious\n\n7. Screen and component priorities\n- Rank which screens/components require the highest UX fidelity first\n- Identify must-have patterns vs secondary enhancements\n\n8. Deliverables for downstream design agents\n- Provide explicit deliverables:\n  - UX brief\n  - flow map\n  - IA/navigation hierarchy\n  - interaction pattern guidelines\n  - motion guidelines\n  - prioritized screen list\n  - component behavior notes\n\nOutput requirements\n- Be concise, structured, and ready for design execution\n- Use clear headings and bullets\n- Optimize for downstream design agents, not stakeholders\n- Do not write implementation code\n- Do not expand scope beyond the listed screens/components\n- Do not introduce playful, trend-driven, or mass-market retail patterns\n```\n\nIf you want, I can also compress this into a **shorter “agent-ready brief” version** of ~150–220 words."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-TroLy","usage":{"input":13406,"output":1505,"totalTokens":17471,"cacheRead":2560,"cacheWrite":0,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775965405625,"responseId":"1775965408885","__openclaw":{"id":"6f8e5def","seq":4}}]},{"key":"agent:ui-ux-pro-max:subagent:9cc5ade0-1d6d-4cc0-8232-5450257406d3","kind":"other","channel":"telegram","spawnedBy":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5212380728","label":"luxury-ecom:ui-ux-pro-max","displayName":"telegram:g-agent-ui-ux-pro-max-subagent-9cc5ade0-1d6d-4cc0-8232-5450257406d3","parentSessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5212380728","deliveryContext":{"channel":"telegram"},"updatedAt":1775965120525,"sessionId":"c22a2990-48e8-47c2-bbe6-3aa7c11f6d1c","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":10326,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"failed","startedAt":1775965047235,"endedAt":1775965092883,"runtimeMs":0,"thinkingLevel":"medium","abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"telegram","transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/ui-ux-pro-max/sessions/c22a2990-48e8-47c2-bbe6-3aa7c11f6d1c.jsonl","messages":[]},{"key":"agent:prompt-optimizer:subagent:9a0bd8d6-856e-4e24-ad1f-007e2908253d","kind":"other","channel":"telegram","spawnedBy":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5212380728","label":"luxury-ecom:prompt-optimizer","displayName":"telegram:g-maiychrus25-company-.ltd","parentSessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5212380728","deliveryContext":{"channel":"telegram"},"updatedAt":1775965054667,"sessionId":"29634186-b281-45ea-b6f7-20b75e2416c3","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":10128,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"failed","startedAt":1775964888321,"endedAt