/ loading / selected / error / success\n  - inventory and checkout-specific states like low stock, sold out, payment processing, order placed\n- Mobile-first component specs for:\n  - header/navigation\n  - hero modules\n  - product tiles\n  - collection cards\n  - search\n  - filter/sort sheets\n  - buttons\n  - inputs/selectors\n  - PDP modules\n  - wishlist/cart\n  - checkout sections\n  - order summary\n  - auth\n  - account/orders\n  - editorial blocks\n  - empty states\n  - badges\n- Accessibility baseline and implementation notes for downstream design/dev work\n\nThe spec is positioned as a token-to-component foundation for Stitch screen generation and frontend implementation."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-TroLy","usage":{"input":10866,"output":283,"totalTokens":24461,"cacheRead":13312,"cacheWrite":0,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775966831958,"responseId":"1775966834471","__openclaw":{"id":"fa93c042","seq":9}}]},{"key":"agent:stitch-design:main","kind":"other","channel":"webchat","displayName":"webchat:g-agent-stitch-design-main","deliveryContext":{"channel":"webchat"},"updatedAt":1775966833663,"sessionId":"8232fb03-6e1d-4e59-9170-ded1fd82e68f","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":39452,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"running","startedAt":1775966833637,"childSessions":["agent:stitch-loop:subagent:94999196-0f5d-4bb4-8535-01303d9ab225"],"abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"webchat","transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/stitch-design/sessions/8232fb03-6e1d-4e59-9170-ded1fd82e68f.jsonl","messages":[]},{"key":"agent:stitch-loop:subagent:94999196-0f5d-4bb4-8535-01303d9ab225","kind":"other","channel":"webchat","spawnedBy":"agent:stitch-design:main","displayName":"webchat:g-agent-stitch-loop-subagent-94999196-0f5d-4bb4-8535-01303d9ab225","parentSessionKey":"agent:stitch-design:main","deliveryContext":{"channel":"webchat"},"updatedAt":1775966805670,"sessionId":"d106b80e-f604-4d49-a7a8-2bf3d753968e","model":"AHV-Holding-TroLy","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":16749,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"done","startedAt":1775966416113,"endedAt":1775966805272,"runtimeMs":345745,"thinkingLevel":"medium","abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"webchat","transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/stitch-loop/sessions/d106b80e-f604-4d49-a7a8-2bf3d753968e.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I could not proceed with the 15-screen sequence because Stitch generation failed immediately on screen 1 (HOME) with the same MCP timeout on all 3 allowed retries, with the required 20-second waits between attempts.\n\nWhat I did:\n- Loaded the required `stitch-loop` skill.\n- Attempted `stitch__generate_screen_from_text` for screen 1 using:\n  - projectId: `12108154905534221530`\n  - deviceType: `MOBILE`\n  - modelId: `GEMINI_3_FLASH`\n- Retries performed exactly as requested:\n  1. Attempt 1 → timed out\n  2. Waited 20s\n  3. Attempt 2 → timed out\n  4. Waited 20s\n  5. Attempt 3 → timed out\n- Then checked project screens once with `stitch__list_screens`, but the tool returned no usable screen listing output.\n\nRelevant detail:\n- Error each time: `MCP error -32001: Request timed out`\n\nNet result:\n- Screens completed: `0/15`\n- Blocking issue: Stitch MCP generation is timing out before I can start the sequence.\n\nIf you want, the next best recovery path is:\n- either retry later when the Stitch MCP backend is responsive,\n- or reduce prompt size / split style tokens into a shorter prompt template and try again,\n- or verify the project/service health from the main agent side before resuming.\n\nI could not complete the 15-screen run because Stitch failed on screen 1.\n\nSummary:\n- Skill loaded: `stitch-loop`\n- Project: `12108154905534221530`\n- Model used: `GEMINI_3_FLASH`\n- Device: `MOBILE`\n\nWhat happened:\n- Screen 1 (HOME) was attempted 3 times\n- Waited 20 seconds between retries as requested\n- All 3 attempts failed with:\n  - `MCP error -32001: Request timed out`\n\nFollow-up check:\n- I called `stitch__list_screens` once to see if the generation may have succeeded despite timeout\n- It returned no usable screen listing output\n\nResult:\n- Completed: `0/15`\n- Blocker: Stitch MCP backend timeout on `generate_screen_from_text`\n\nRecommended next step:\n- Retry later when Stitch MCP is responsive, or\n- have the main agent try a shorter prompt/versioning strategy before resuming the full 15-screen sequence."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-TroLy","usage":{"input":2285,"output":524,"totalTokens":17273,"cacheRead":14464,"cacheWrite":0,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775966778444,"responseId":"1775966779623","__openclaw":{"id":"3a8dbcba","seq":16}}]},{"key":"agent:ui-design-system:main","kind":"other","channel":"unknown","updatedAt":1775965906153,"sessionId":"aa862f9c-22aa-4dd7-baa2-fdd1c0b705e8","model":"AHV-Holding-TroLy","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":22926,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"failed","startedAt":1775965627842,"endedAt":1775965891137,"runtimeMs":263295,"abortedLastRun":false,"transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/ui-design-system/sessions/aa862f9c-22aa-4dd7-baa2-fdd1c0b705e8.jsonl","messages":[]},{"key":"agent:ui-ux-pro-max:subagent:d533555e-8a84-4f30-a0a1-a2bc93b09026","kind":"other","channel":"telegram","spawnedBy":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5212380728","label":"luxury-ecom:ui-ux-pro-max","displayName":"telegram:g-agent-ui-ux-pro-max-subagent-d533555e-8a84-4f30-a0a1-a2bc93b09026","parentSessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5212380728","deliveryContext":{"channel":"telegram"},"updatedAt":1775965666810,"sessionId":"d29502b2-d96e-4109-9756-87d40880ec0b","model":"AHV-Holding-TroLy","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":47241,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"done","startedAt":1775965206375,"endedAt":1775965657795,"runtimeMs":432789,"thinkingLevel":"medium","abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"telegram","transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/ui-ux-pro-max/sessions/d29502b2-d96e-4109-9756-87d40880ec0b.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Completed:\n- Read and applied the `ui-ux-pro-max` skill.\n- Produced a full UX direction document for the luxury e-commerce app.\n- Wrote it to:\n  - `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/HANDOVER.md`\n- Dispatched downstream agent turns:\n  - `ui-design-system` with the HANDOVER content\n  - `stitch-design` with the full Stitch generation brief for `projects/12108154905534221530`\n\nKey contents in the handover:\n- Browse → discover → decide → purchase → track flows\n- Mobile-first IA and nav hierarchy\n- Interaction rules: 44x44 targets, gestures, loading/feedback states\n- Luxury motion guidelines\n- Luxury-specific UX principles\n- Screen-by-screen intent and downstream instructions\n\nRelevant note:\n- The workspace protocol required `prompt-optimizer` first; I initiated that agent turn as well, but it was still waiting on reply when I completed the requested deliverables and downstream dispatches."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-TroLy","usage":{"input":2185,"output":217,"totalTokens":47458,"cacheRead":45056,"cacheWrite":0,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775965633117,"responseId":"1775965634449","__openclaw":{"id":"5c86bbf5","seq":28}}]},{"key":"agent:prompt-optimizer:main","kind":"other","channel":"unknown","updatedAt":1775965481997,"sessionId":"2c50e4c8-6c71-45da-8c3f-4e76697147e7","model":"AHV-Holding-TroLy","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":15966,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"done","startedAt":1775965397801,"endedAt":1775965481635,"runtimeMs":83834,"abortedLastRun":false,"transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/prompt-optimizer/sessions/2c50e4c8-6c71-45da-8c3f-4e76697147e7.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":" **Section 1: Prompt Diagnosis**\n\n**Strengths:** Strong brand direction, clear screen/component scope, defined palette/typography/motion, and explicit UX tasks.\n\n**Issues:**\n\n| Issue | Impact | Suggested Fix |\n|---|---|---|\n| No primary business goal stated | Agents may optimize for aesthetics over conversion | Add measurable UX/commercial objectives |\n| Audience is broad | Luxury positioning may become generic | Specify expectations for affluent, high-intent shoppers |\n| Priorities are not ranked | Agents may overinvest in low-value screens | State must-have vs secondary outputs |\n| Constraints are incomplete | Outputs may drift into non-luxury patterns | Add accessibility, mobile-first, restraint, and no-discount-noise rules |\n| Deliverables are implied, not explicit | Downstream outputs may be inconsistent | Define exact artifacts required |\n\n**Needs Clarification:**\n1. Should the experience emphasize brand discovery/editorial storytelling equally with conversion, or conversion first?\n2. Are promotions/discount-first patterns intentionally excluded to preserve luxury positioning?\n3. Should agents produce wire-level UX guidance only, or also content direction/microcopy tone?\n\n---\n\n**Section 2: Recommended Components**\n\n| Type | Component | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| Skill | `@prompt-optimizer` | Refines the brief into a copy-paste downstream agent prompt |\n| Skill | `@ui-design-system` | Interprets visual system, component hierarchy, and luxury UI direction |\n| Skill | `@senior-architect` | Structures IA, flows, and interaction system coherently |\n| Skill | `@master-orchestrator` | Useful if multiple design agents will split screens, flows, and system guidance |\n\n---\n\n**Section 3: Optimized Prompt — Full Version**\n\n```text\nCreate a concise UX direction brief for downstream design agents for a mobile-first premium luxury e-commerce app.\n\nContext\n- App type: premium luxury e-commerce\n- Target users: affluent men and women with high purchase intent, strong brand sensitivity, and expectation of polish, trust, and exclusivity\n- Brand attributes: premium, minimal, editorial, exclusive, timeless\n- Visual tone: quiet luxury, not flashy; refined, restrained, and high-end\n\nDesign foundations\n- Primary color: black #0B0B0C\n- Support palette:\n  - soft gold #C6A972\n  - ivory #F6F1E8\n  - warm white #FAF8F4\n  - charcoal #1A1A1D\n  - muted gray #8C8C8F\n- Typography:\n  - headings: elegant serif\n  - body/UI: modern sans-serif\n- Motion:\n  - soft, restrained, luxurious\n  - use fade-ins, gentle hover lifts, smooth transitions\n  - avoid energetic, playful, or attention-seeking animation\n\nScreen scope\n- Home\n- Collection / Category Listing\n- Search\n- Product Detail\n- Wishlist\n- Cart\n- Checkout\n- Sign In\n- Sign Up\n- Forgot Password\n- Profile / Account\n- Order History\n- Order Detail\n- Featured Collection Landing\n- Editorial Campaign Page\n\nComponent scope\n- Navigation\n- Hero banners\n- Category cards\n- Product tiles\n- Filters and sort\n- Buttons\n- Form inputs\n- Badges / labels\n- Empty states\n- Checkout sections\n- Order summaries\n- Wishlist\n- Cart\n- Footer\n- Editorial panels\n\nPrimary objectives\n1. Deliver a luxury-first browsing and shopping experience that feels exclusive, calm, and premium.\n2. Balance editorial brand storytelling with frictionless commerce.\n3. Help users move confidently from browse → discover → decide → purchase → track.\n4. Increase clarity, trust, and purchase intent without visual clutter.\n\nUX priorities\n1. Mobile-first clarity and elegance\n2. Premium perception through restraint, spacing, hierarchy, and imagery treatment\n3. Fast product discovery and confident product evaluation\n4. Seamless checkout with minimal friction\n5. Strong account and order-tracking usability\n6. Consistent luxury tone across utility screens, not just marketing pages\n\nConstraints\n- Mobile-first; prioritize handheld interactions before larger breakpoints\n- Maintain a minimal editorial aesthetic across all screens\n- Avoid discount-heavy, noisy, mass-market e-commerce patterns\n- Preserve strong readability and accessibility\n- Use touch targets of at least 44px\n- Keep navigation simple, predictable, and unobtrusive\n- Motion must support polish, not spectacle\n- Favor whitespace, typography, and image-led hierarchy over dense UI chrome\n\nRequired outputs\nProduce a clarified UX brief with these sections:\n\n1. Objectives\n- Summarize the experience goals in 4–6 bullets\n\n2. Experience principles for luxury commerce\n- Define 5–7 UX principles tailored to luxury retail\n- Examples: restraint, confidence, trust, editorial hierarchy, premium pacing, tactile clarity\n\n3. User flow map\n- Define the end-to-end flow: browse → discover → decide → purchase → track\n- Include key decision points, friction risks, and moments where luxury perception must be preserved\n\n4. Information architecture and navigation hierarchy\n- Define top-level navigation, secondary navigation, account/order areas, and cross-links between editorial and commerce\n- Clarify how users move between Home, Collection, Search, PDP, Wishlist, Cart, Checkout, and Account\n\n5. Interaction patterns\n- Define:\n  - tap target minimums\n  - gesture usage\n  - filter/sort behavior\n  - search behavior\n  - wishlist/cart interactions\n  - form behavior\n  - validation and error handling\n  - loading, empty, and success states\n- Keep patterns premium, calm, and predictable\n\n6. Motion guidelines\n- Specify animation principles, timing feel, where motion is appropriate, and where it should be avoided\n- Keep motion subtle and luxurious\n\n7. Screen and component priorities\n- Rank which screens/components require the highest UX fidelity first\n- Identify must-have patterns vs secondary enhancements\n\n8. Deliverables for downstream design agents\n- Provide explicit deliverables:\n  - UX brief\n  - flow map\n  - IA/navigation hierarchy\n  - interaction pattern guidelines\n  - motion guidelines\n  - prioritized screen list\n  - component behavior notes\n\nOutput requirements\n- Be concise, structured, and ready for design execution\n- Use clear headings and bullets\n- Optimize for downstream design agents, not stakeholders\n- Do not write implementation code\n- Do not expand scope beyond the listed screens/components\n- Do not introduce playful, trend-driven, or mass-market retail patterns\n```\n\nIf you want, I can also compress this into a **shorter “agent-ready brief” version** of ~150–220 words."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-TroLy","usage":{"input":13406,"output":1505,"totalTokens":17471,"cacheRead":2560,"cacheWrite":0,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775965405625,"responseId":"1775965408885","__openclaw":{"id":"6f8e5def","seq":4}}]},{"key":"agent:ui-ux-pro-max:subagent:9cc5ade0-1d6d-4cc0-8232-5450257406d3","kind":"other","channel":"telegram","spawnedBy":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5212380728","label":"luxury-ecom:ui-ux-pro-max","displayName":"telegram:g-agent-ui-ux-pro-max-subagent-9cc5ade0-1d6d-4cc0-8232-5450257406d3","parentSessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5212380728","deliveryContext":{"channel":"telegram"},"updatedAt":1775965120525,"sessionId":"c22a2990-48e8-47c2-bbe6-3aa7c11f6d1c","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":10326,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"failed","startedAt":1775965047235,"endedAt":1775965092883,"runtimeMs":0,"thinkingLevel":"medium","abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"telegram","transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/ui-ux-pro-max/sessions/c22a2990-48e8-47c2-bbe6-3aa7c11f6d1c.jsonl","messages":[]}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775968378993}}
{"type":"message","id":"23cff6ca","parentId":"43035b83","timestamp":"2026-04-12T04:33:18.041Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the full picture. Let me analyze the current state:\n\n1. `stitch-design:main` is still running (has a child session `stitch-loop:subagent:94999196...`)\n2. `stitch-loop:subagent:...` has completed with 0/15 screens generated due to Stitch MCP timeout errors\n\nThe key finding from `stitch-loop`:\n- Attempted 3 times to generate HOME screen\n- All 3 attempts failed with `MCP error -32001: Request timed out`\n- No screens were generated\n\n`stitch-design:main` is still running and has `stitch-loop` as a child session. \n\nSo `stitch-design` is actively managing the screen generation workflow while `stitch-loop` has exhausted its retries and shut down. The bottleneck is clearly Stitch's MCP endpoint timing out on every request.\n\nI need to be direct with the user: the design pipeline finished its work, but Stitch screen generation is blocked by these timeout errors. The Stitch backend itself appears to be struggling, so I could either retry the generation attempt or pivot to using the design system documents as the foundation for manual implementation.","thinkingSignature":"e1461c23042ed8a3914eec3c794d3e477eaa33a12f9e87a9359121e9e452aba8"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] 📊 **Pipeline Status — cập nhật**\n\n| Bước | Agent | Trạng thái |\n|------|-------|-----------|\n| 1 | `prompt-optimizer` | ✅ Hoàn thành |\n| 2 | `ui-ux-pro-max` | ✅ Hoàn thành — UX direction |\n| 3 | `ui-design-system` | ✅ Hoàn thành — Design tokens |\n| 4 | `stitch-design` | ⚠️ **Bị chặn** — Stitch MCP backend timeout |\n\n**Vấn đề cốt lõi:** Stitch generation liên tục timeout (`MCP error -32001`) dù thử 3 lần. Stitch backend không phản hỏi kịp.\n\n**Đã hoàn thành đầy đủ:**\n- `HANDOVER.md` — UX direction đầy đủ\n- `DESIGN_SYSTEM.md` — tokens, type scale, spacing, component specs\n\n**Cần quyết định:**\n1. **Retry Stitch** — thử lại generation sau\n2. **Dùng design docs làm spec** — chuyển sang `senior-frontend` build UI thủ công từ spec\n3. **Kiểm tra Stitch backend** — xem server Stitch có online không\n\nBạn muốn đi hướng nào?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":7043,"output":560,"cacheRead":59258,"cacheWrite":553,"totalTokens":67414,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775968379008,"responseId":"062a537c56d9fccc09697ec6b7f86181"}}
