{"type":"message","id":"9d96753e","parentId":"abf2a75f","timestamp":"2026-04-12T06:00:38.122Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_8mgrhfyhv68i_1","toolName":"stitch__get_project","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"name\":\"projects/13261989784115652519\",\"title\":\"Luxury E-commerce UI Kit\",\"visibility\":\"PRIVATE\",\"createTime\":\"2026-04-12T03:21:20.339714Z\",\"updateTime\":\"2026-04-12T05:59:38.066678Z\",\"projectType\":\"TEXT_TO_UI_PRO\",\"thumbnailScreenshot\":{\"name\":\"projects/13261989784115652519/files/8eac88e9de0244ff82dd953738f11bb8\",\"downloadUrl\":\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/aida/ADBb0ujE5V0nQlZl4lfY-s3OjdTe1gMVW5GI7OnASy56DmbQvQnYPAjBax7eeHmPekjSUMbAVq5UVQWzTOzihJ78XI9xoSKRc-w_H4TKE3_W5-NNk3hO62_4ugtHjpIDvdckqqwHbL373LTpn42uvp9Nb2n340lMuFXue1CkOtXHysDxIDzJCOC7qOaZbKtzhLJiseoAXc-dQW14J4lrPHKh9xYcFCxAY_lJIBMjsReTMfi1ERgfOIS7O2JF-yVu\"},\"origin\":\"STITCH\",\"deviceType\":\"DESKTOP\",\"designTheme\":{\"colorMode\":\"LIGHT\",\"font\":\"NOTO_SERIF\",\"customColor\":\"#000000\",\"headlineFont\":\"NOTO_SERIF\",\"bodyFont\":\"MANROPE\",\"labelFont\":\"MANROPE\",\"namedColors\":{\"background\":\"#f9f9f9\",\"error\":\"#9e3f4e\",\"error_container\":\"#ff8b9a\",\"error_dim\":\"#4f0116\",\"inverse_on_surface\":\"#9c9d9d\",\"inverse_primary\":\"#ffffff\",\"inverse_surface\":\"#0c0f0f\",\"on_background\":\"#2d3435\",\"on_error\":\"#fff7f7\",\"on_error_container\":\"#782232\",\"on_primary\":\"#f8f8f8\",\"on_primary_container\":\"#525252\",\"on_primary_fixed\":\"#3f3f3f\",\"on_primary_fixed_variant\":\"#5b5b5b\",\"on_secondary\":\"#fff8ef\",\"on_secondary_container\":\"#644f00\",\"on_secondary_fixed\":\"#4e3d00\",\"on_secondary_fixed_variant\":\"#705900\",\"on_surface\":\"#2d3435\",\"on_surface_variant\":\"#5a6061\",\"on_tertiary\":\"#fbf8f8\",\"on_tertiary_container\":\"#5c5b5b\",\"on_tertiary_fixed\":\"#4a4949\",\"on_tertiary_fixed_variant\":\"#676666\",\"outline\":\"#757c7d\",\"outline_variant\":\"#adb3b4\",\"primary\":\"#5e5e5e\",\"primary_container\":\"#e2e2e2\",\"primary_dim\":\"#525252\",\"primary_fixed\":\"#e2e2e2\",\"primary_fixed_dim\":\"#d4d4d4\",\"secondary\":\"#745c00\",\"secondary_container\":\"#ffe088\",\"secondary_dim\":\"#665100\",\"secondary_fixed\":\"#ffe088\",\"secondary_fixed_dim\":\"#f8d056\",\"surface\":\"#f9f9f9\",\"surface_bright\":\"#f9f9f9\",\"surface_container\":\"#ebeeef\",\"surface_container_high\":\"#e4e9ea\",\"surface_container_highest\":\"#dde4e5\",\"surface_container_low\":\"#f2f4f4\",\"surface_container_lowest\":\"#ffffff\",\"surface_dim\":\"#d3dbdd\",\"surface_tint\":\"#5e5e5e\",\"surface_variant\":\"#dde4e5\",\"tertiary\":\"#5f5f5f\",\"tertiary_container\":\"#f6f3f2\",\"tertiary_dim\":\"#535353\",\"tertiary_fixed\":\"#f6f3f2\",\"tertiary_fixed_dim\":\"#e7e5e4\"},\"designMd\":\"```markdown\\n# Design System Document: The Cinematic Editorial\\n\\n## 1. Overview & Creative North Star: \\\"The Digital Curator\\\"\\nThis design system is not a store; it is a digital gallery. Our Creative North Star is **The Digital Curator**. We move away from the cluttered, \\\"conversion-optimized\\\" templates of standard e-commerce and toward a high-end, editorial experience that feels like a luxury coffee-table book.\\n\\nThe system breaks the \\\"template\\\" look through **Intentional Asymmetry**. Large-scale product imagery should bleed off the grid or overlap with serif typography to create a sense of depth and motion. We prioritize \\\"The Breath\\\"—generous, unencumbered whitespace—that signals to the affluent shopper that we are not in a rush to sell, but rather to present.\\n\\n## 2. Colors: Tonal Depth & The \\\"No-Line\\\" Rule\\nThe palette is rooted in deep blacks and warm, light-reflective neutrals. We use Material Design token logic to create a sophisticated, layered environment.\\n\\n### Color Tokens\\n*   **Primary (#5e5e5e):** Used for core UI logic; a refined charcoal that avoids the harshness of true black in functional elements.\\n*   **Secondary (#745c00 / Soft Gold):** Reserved exclusively for \\\"Moments of Truth\\\"—active states, premium CTA accents, or luxury signifiers.\\n*   **Surface (#f9f9f9):** Our \\\"Ivory\\\" base. It provides a warmer, more expensive feel than a clinical \\\"Pure White.\\\"\\n\\n### The \\\"No-Line\\\" Rule\\n**Prohibit 1px solid borders for sectioning.** To maintain the cinematic feel, boundaries must be defined solely through background color shifts.\\n*   Use `surface-container-low` (#f2f4f4) for secondary content sections.\\n*   Use `surface-container-highest` (#dde4e5) for utility bars or footers.\\n*   Transitions between sections should feel like the turning of a heavy, matte paper page, not a digital box.\\n\\n### The \\\"Glass & Gradient\\\" Rule\\nFor floating elements (modals, navigation overlays), utilize **Glassmorphism**. Apply `surface` colors at 80% opacity with a `20px` backdrop blur. This allows the high-end product photography to \\\"ghost\\\" through the UI, maintaining the cinematic immersion. For main CTAs, use a subtle linear gradient from `primary` to `primary_dim` to give a tactile, \\\"satin\\\" finish.\\n\\n## 3. Typography: The High-Contrast Dialogue\\nThe typography system is a dialogue between the classical (Noto Serif) and the industrial (Manrope).\\n\\n*   **Display & Headlines (Noto Serif):** These are our \\\"Voice.\\\" Used for editorial storytelling and product titles. The high-contrast serifs should be set with tight tracking (-2%) to feel like a fashion masthead.\\n*   **Body & UI (Manrope):** These are our \\\"Function.\\\" Used for descriptions and technical data. Manrope’s geometric clarity ensures legibility against complex imagery.\\n*   **Hierarchy as Identity:** \\n    *   `display-lg` (3.5rem) should be used sparingly, often overlapping image containers.\\n    *   `label-sm` (0.6875rem) in all-caps with increased letter spacing (+10%) should be used for \\\"Exclusive\\\" or \\\"Limited Edition\\\" tags.\\n\\n## 4. Elevation & Depth: Tonal Layering\\nWe reject the heavy drop-shadows of the 2010s. Depth is achieved through \\\"stacking\\\" surfaces.\\n\\n*   **The Layering Principle:** Place a `surface-container-lowest` (#ffffff) card on top of a `surface-container-low` (#f2f4f4) section. The slight shift in \\\"Ivory\\\" creates a natural, soft lift.\\n*   **Ambient Shadows:** If an element must float (e.g., a luxury cart drawer), use an extra-diffused shadow: `box-shadow: 0 20px 50px rgba(45, 52, 53, 0.04);`. The shadow color is a tint of `on_surface`, not grey.\\n*   **The \\\"Ghost Border\\\" Fallback:** If a border is required for accessibility (e.g., input fields), use the `outline-variant` (#adb3b4) at 15% opacity. **Never use 100% opaque borders.**\\n\\n## 5. Components\\n\\n### Buttons\\n*   **Primary:** Solid `primary` (#5e5e5e) with `on_primary` (#f8f8f8) text. 0px border radius. High-padding (16px 32px) to feel expansive.\\n*   **Secondary:** Ghost style. `outline` (#757c7d) at 20% opacity. On hover, the background shifts to `surface-container-high`.\\n*   **Tertiary:** Underlined `label-md` text. The underline should be 1px and offset by 4px.\\n\\n### Inputs & Fields\\n*   **Text Inputs:** No background. Only a bottom border using `outline-variant` at 20%. The label should use `notoSerif` for a bespoke, \\\"signed\\\" feel.\\n*   **Error States:** Use `error` (#9e3f4e) for text, but never a red box. Use a subtle `error_container` (#ff8b9a) background fill at 10% opacity.\\n\\n### Cards & Lists\\n*   **Editorial Cards:** Forbid dividers. Use `surface-container` tiers to distinguish the product from the background. \\n*   **Imagery:** All cards must use a 4:5 or 1:1 aspect ratio. Images should include a subtle `0.5s` scale-up transition on hover to simulate a \\\"lens zoom.\\\"\\n\\n### Specialized Component: The \\\"Cinematic Scroller\\\"\\nA horizontal product list where the images are not clipped by a container, but fade into the `surface` color using a linear-gradient mask on the right edge. This encourages \\\"discovery\\\" rather than \\\"scrolling.\\\"\\n\\n## 6. Do's and Don'ts\\n\\n### Do\\n*   **Do** use asymmetrical margins (e.g., 10% left, 15% right) for hero sections to break the \\\"web\\\" feel.\\n*   **Do** use \\\"Warm White\\\" (#FDFDFD) for text on dark backgrounds to avoid eye strain.\\n*   **Do** ensure all interactions (hovers, fades) have a duration of at least `400ms` with an `ease-in-out` curve to feel \\\"heavy\\\" and expensive.\\n\\n### Don't\\n*   **Don't** use standard 4px or 8px border-radii. This system is **Strict 0px (Square)**. Luxury is sharp and intentional.\\n*   **Don't** use \\\"Sale Red.\\\" Use `secondary_fixed` (Soft Gold) for promotions.\\n*   **Don't** use icon-only buttons. Affluence expects clear, curated labeling. Always accompany icons with a `label-sm` text element.\\n*   **Don't** use divider lines to separate list items. Use the spacing scale (`24px` or `32px` gaps) to let the content breathe.```\",\"colorVariant\":\"NEUTRAL\",\"overridePrimaryColor\":\"#000000\",\"overrideSecondaryColor\":\"#D4AF37\",\"overrideTertiaryColor\":\"#333333\",\"overrideNeutralColor\":\"#FDFDFD\",\"spacingScale\":3},\"screenInstances\":[{\"id\":\"8c9d0982820e4ae595f67351cb9a64ce\",\"sourceScreen\":\"projects/13261989784115652519/screens/8c9d0982820e4ae595f67351cb9a64ce\",\"x\":3712,\"width\":1280,\"height\":5024},{\"id\":\"90b02627a325484f845073e4815fb552\",\"sourceScreen\":\"projects/13261989784115652519/screens/90b02627a325484f845073e4815fb552\",\"x\":7744,\"width\":1280,\"height\":2028},{\"id\":\"ad2b64b932fb4b7980ef450ef3ac6db9\",\"sourceScreen\":\"projects/13261989784115652519/screens/ad2b64b932fb4b7980ef450ef3ac6db9\",\"x\":6400,\"width\":1280,\"height\":2095},{\"id\":\"assets-40e982ef8dfb4af2ab0af498ef8cfff6-1775964104766\",\"width\":960,\"height\":540,\"sourceAsset\":\"assets/40e982ef8dfb4af2ab0af498ef8cfff6\",\"type\":\"DESIGN_SYSTEM_INSTANCE\"},{\"id\":\"cf13932445dd4ceeb7a0a9b9834ea7b0\",\"sourceScreen\":\"projects/13261989784115652519/screens/cf13932445dd4ceeb7a0a9b9834ea7b0\",\"x\":1024,\"width\":1280,\"height\":1989},{\"id\":\"e283104138994d29b2075d9ccc937c7b\",\"sourceScreen\":\"projects/13261989784115652519/screens/e283104138994d29b2075d9ccc937c7b\",\"x\":5056,\"width\":1280,\"height\":1024},{\"id\":\"e75ed29a22d249a5bc79a96ad663b95f\",\"sourceScreen\":\"projects/13261989784115652519/screens/e75ed29a22d249a5bc79a96ad663b95f\",\"x\":2368,\"width\":1280,\"height\":3214}],\"metadata\":{\"userRole\":\"OWNER\"}}"}],"details":{"mcpServer":"stitch","mcpTool":"get_project","structuredContent":{"createTime":"2026-04-12T03:21:20.339714Z","designTheme":{"bodyFont":"MANROPE","colorMode":"LIGHT","colorVariant":"NEUTRAL","customColor":"#000000","designMd":"```markdown\n# Design System Document: The Cinematic Editorial\n\n## 1. Overview & Creative North Star: \"The Digital Curator\"\nThis design system is not a store; it is a digital gallery. Our Creative North Star is **The Digital Curator**. We move away from the cluttered, \"conversion-optimized\" templates of standard e-commerce and toward a high-end, editorial experience that feels like a luxury coffee-table book.\n\nThe system breaks the \"template\" look through **Intentional Asymmetry**. Large-scale product imagery should bleed off the grid or overlap with serif typography to create a sense of depth and motion. We prioritize \"The Breath\"—generous, unencumbered whitespace—that signals to the affluent shopper that we are not in a rush to sell, but rather to present.\n\n## 2. Colors: Tonal Depth & The \"No-Line\" Rule\nThe palette is rooted in deep blacks and warm, light-reflective neutrals. We use Material Design token logic to create a sophisticated, layered environment.\n\n### Color Tokens\n*   **Primary (#5e5e5e):** Used for core UI logic; a refined charcoal that avoids the harshness of true black in functional elements.\n*   **Secondary (#745c00 / Soft Gold):** Reserved exclusively for \"Moments of Truth\"—active states, premium CTA accents, or luxury signifiers.\n*   **Surface (#f9f9f9):** Our \"Ivory\" base. It provides a warmer, more expensive feel than a clinical \"Pure White.\"\n\n### The \"No-Line\" Rule\n**Prohibit 1px solid borders for sectioning.** To maintain the cinematic feel, boundaries must be defined solely through background color shifts.\n*   Use `surface-container-low` (#f2f4f4) for secondary content sections.\n*   Use `surface-container-highest` (#dde4e5) for utility bars or footers.\n*   Transitions between sections should feel like the turning of a heavy, matte paper page, not a digital box.\n\n### The \"Glass & Gradient\" Rule\nFor floating elements (modals, navigation overlays), utilize **Glassmorphism**. Apply `surface` colors at 80% opacity with a `20px` backdrop blur. This allows the high-end product photography to \"ghost\" through the UI, maintaining the cinematic immersion. For main CTAs, use a subtle linear gradient from `primary` to `primary_dim` to give a tactile, \"satin\" finish.\n\n## 3. Typography: The High-Contrast Dialogue\nThe typography system is a dialogue between the classical (Noto Serif) and the industrial (Manrope).\n\n*   **Display & Headlines (Noto Serif):** These are our \"Voice.\" Used for editorial storytelling and product titles. The high-contrast serifs should be set with tight tracking (-2%) to feel like a fashion masthead.\n*   **Body & UI (Manrope):** These are our \"Function.\" Used for descriptions and technical data. Manrope’s geometric clarity ensures legibility against complex imagery.\n*   **Hierarchy as Identity:** \n    *   `display-lg` (3.5rem) should be used sparingly, often overlapping image containers.\n    *   `label-sm` (0.6875rem) in all-caps with increased letter spacing (+10%) should be used for \"Exclusive\" or \"Limited Edition\" tags.\n\n## 4. Elevation & Depth: Tonal Layering\nWe reject the heavy drop-shadows of the 2010s. Depth is achieved through \"stacking\" surfaces.\n\n*   **The Layering Principle:** Place a `surface-container-lowest` (#ffffff) card on top of a `surface-container-low` (#f2f4f4) section. The slight shift in \"Ivory\" creates a natural, soft lift.\n*   **Ambient Shadows:** If an element must float (e.g., a luxury cart drawer), use an extra-diffused shadow: `box-shadow: 0 20px 50px rgba(45, 52, 53, 0.04);`. The shadow color is a tint of `on_surface`, not grey.\n*   **The \"Ghost Border\" Fallback:** If a border is required for accessibility (e.g., input fields), use the `outline-variant` (#adb3b4) at 15% opacity. **Never use 100% opaque borders.**\n\n## 5. Components\n\n### Buttons\n*   **Primary:** Solid `primary` (#5e5e5e) with `on_primary` (#f8f8f8) text. 0px border radius. High-padding (16px 32px) to feel expansive.\n*   **Secondary:** Ghost style. `outline` (#757c7d) at 20% opacity. On hover, the background shifts to `surface-container-high`.\n*   **Tertiary:** Underlined `label-md` text. The underline should be 1px and offset by 4px.\n\n### Inputs & Fields\n*   **Text Inputs:** No background. Only a bottom border using `outline-variant` at 20%. The label should use `notoSerif` for a bespoke, \"signed\" feel.\n*   **Error States:** Use `error` (#9e3f4e) for text, but never a red box. Use a subtle `error_container` (#ff8b9a) background fill at 10% opacity.\n\n### Cards & Lists\n*   **Editorial Cards:** Forbid dividers. Use `surface-container` tiers to distinguish the product from the background. \n*   **Imagery:** All cards must use a 4:5 or 1:1 aspect ratio. Images should include a subtle `0.5s` scale-up transition on hover to simulate a \"lens zoom.\"\n\n### Specialized Component: The \"Cinematic Scroller\"\nA horizontal product list where the images are not clipped by a container, but fade into the `surface` color using a linear-gradient mask on the right edge. This encourages \"discovery\" rather than \"scrolling.\"\n\n## 6. Do's and Don'ts\n\n### Do\n*   **Do** use asymmetrical margins (e.g., 10% left, 15% right) for hero sections to break the \"web\" feel.\n*   **Do** use \"Warm White\" (#FDFDFD) for text on dark backgrounds to avoid eye strain.\n*   **Do** ensure all interactions (hovers, fades) have a duration of at least `400ms` with an `ease-in-out` curve to feel \"heavy\" and expensive.\n\n### Don't\n*   **Don't** use standard 4px or 8px border-radii. This system is **Strict 0px (Square)**. Luxury is sharp and intentional.\n*   **Don't** use \"Sale Red.\" Use `secondary_fixed` (Soft Gold) for promotions.\n*   **Don't** use icon-only buttons. Affluence expects clear, curated labeling. Always accompany icons with a `label-sm` text element.\n*   **Don't** use divider lines to separate list items. Use the spacing scale (`24px` or `32px` gaps) to let the content breathe.```","font":"NOTO_SERIF","headlineFont":"NOTO_SERIF","labelFont":"MANROPE","namedColors":{"background":"#f9f9f9","error":"#9e3f4e","error_container":"#ff8b9a","error_dim":"#4f0116","inverse_on_surface":"#9c9d9d","inverse_primary":"#ffffff","inverse_surface":"#0c0f0f","on_background":"#2d3435","on_error":"#fff7f7","on_error_container":"#782232","on_primary":"#f8f8f8","on_primary_container":"#525252","on_primary_fixed":"#3f3f3f","on_primary_fixed_variant":"#5b5b5b","on_secondary":"#fff8ef","on_secondary_container":"#644f00","on_secondary_fixed":"#4e3d00","on_secondary_fixed_variant":"#705900","on_surface":"#2d3435","on_surface_variant":"#5a6061","on_tertiary":"#fbf8f8","on_tertiary_container":"#5c5b5b","on_tertiary_fixed":"#4a4949","on_tertiary_fixed_variant":"#676666","outline":"#757c7d","outline_variant":"#adb3b4","primary":"#5e5e5e","primary_container":"#e2e2e2","primary_dim":"#525252","primary_fixed":"#e2e2e2","primary_fixed_dim":"#d4d4d4","secondary":"#745c00","secondary_container":"#ffe088","secondary_dim":"#665100","secondary_fixed":"#ffe088","secondary_fixed_dim":"#f8d056","surface":"#f9f9f9","surface_bright":"#f9f9f9","surface_container":"#ebeeef","surface_container_high":"#e4e9ea","surface_container_highest":"#dde4e5","surface_container_low":"#f2f4f4","surface_container_lowest":"#ffffff","surface_dim":"#d3dbdd","surface_tint":"#5e5e5e","surface_variant":"#dde4e5","tertiary":"#5f5f5f","tertiary_container":"#f6f3f2","tertiary_dim":"#535353","tertiary_fixed":"#f6f3f2","tertiary_fixed_dim":"#e7e5e4"},"overrideNeutralColor":"#FDFDFD","overridePrimaryColor":"#000000","overrideSecondaryColor":"#D4AF37","overrideTertiaryColor":"#333333","spacingScale":3},"deviceType":"DESKTOP","metadata":{"userRole":"OWNER"},"name":"projects/13261989784115652519","origin":"STITCH","projectType":"TEXT_TO_UI_PRO","screenInstances":[{"height":5024,"id":"8c9d0982820e4ae595f67351cb9a64ce","sourceScreen":"projects/13261989784115652519/screens/8c9d0982820e4ae595f67351cb9a64ce","width":1280,"x":3712},{"height":2028,"id":"90b02627a325484f845073e4815fb552","sourceScreen":"projects/13261989784115652519/screens/90b02627a325484f845073e4815fb552","width":1280,"x":7744},{"height":2095,"id":"ad2b64b932fb4b7980ef450ef3ac6db9","sourceScreen":"projects/13261989784115652519/screens/ad2b64b932fb4b7980ef450ef3ac6db9","width":1280,"x":6400},{"height":540,"id":"assets-40e982ef8dfb4af2ab0af498ef8cfff6-1775964104766","sourceAsset":"assets/40e982ef8dfb4af2ab0af498ef8cfff6","type":"DESIGN_SYSTEM_INSTANCE","width":960},{"height":1989,"id":"cf13932445dd4ceeb7a0a9b9834ea7b0","sourceScreen":"projects/13261989784115652519/screens/cf13932445dd4ceeb7a0a9b9834ea7b0","width":1280,"x":1024},{"height":1024,"id":"e283104138994d29b2075d9ccc937c7b","sourceScreen":"projects/13261989784115652519/screens/e283104138994d29b2075d9ccc937c7b","width":1280,"x":5056},{"height":3214,"id":"e75ed29a22d249a5bc79a96ad663b95f","sourceScreen":"projects/13261989784115652519/screens/e75ed29a22d249a5bc79a96ad663b95f","width":1280,"x":2368}],"thumbnailScreenshot":{"downloadUrl":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/aida/ADBb0ujE5V0nQlZl4lfY-s3OjdTe1gMVW5GI7OnASy56DmbQvQnYPAjBax7eeHmPekjSUMbAVq5UVQWzTOzihJ78XI9xoSKRc-w_H4TKE3_W5-NNk3hO62_4ugtHjpIDvdckqqwHbL373LTpn42uvp9Nb2n340lMuFXue1CkOtXHysDxIDzJCOC7qOaZbKtzhLJiseoAXc-dQW14J4lrPHKh9xYcFCxAY_lJIBMjsReTMfi1ERgfOIS7O2JF-yVu","name":"projects/13261989784115652519/files/8eac88e9de0244ff82dd953738f11bb8"},"title":"Luxury E-commerce UI Kit","updateTime":"2026-04-12T05:59:38.066678Z","visibility":"PRIVATE"}},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775973638118}}
{"type":"message","id":"a95b8a73","parentId":"9d96753e","timestamp":"2026-04-12T06:00:49.876Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Excellent! The user has selected this design as their reference. It's a \"Luxury E-commerce UI Kit\" with:\n- **Design System:** \"The Cinematic Editorial\" / \"Digital Curator\"\n- **Colors:** Charcoal primary (#5e5e5e), Soft Gold secondary (#745c00/#D4AF37), Ivory surface (#f9f9f9)\n- **Typography:** Noto Serif (headlines) + Manrope (body/UI)\n- **Key rules:** No 1px borders, glassmorphism for floating elements, strict 0px border radius, ambient shadows, editorial cards, cinematic scroller, warm white text on dark backgrounds\n\n\n- **Design tokens:** 8 existing screens with a detailed design specification already documented\n\nNow I'm reviewing the available screens and the comprehensive design system documentation to understand what we're working with before regenerating the screens in the target project with this reference applied.\n\nActually, I realize I can apply the design system directly to our project using the `stitch__apply_design_system` tool—I'll use the design system from the reference project (ID: 40e982ef8dfb4af2ab0af498ef8cfff6) and apply it to our 15 luxury e-commerce screens. I need to retrieve the actual design system asset ID first by checking the project details or listing its design systems, then I can proceed with the application.","thinkingSignature":"e249612b9b4ca52b5715fcfee05c73fe2b5b6ea898bb2986d8789d2c6af2e65c"},{"type":"text","text":"Tuyệt vời — đây là design system **\"The Cinematic Editorial\"** cực kỳ phù hợp. Để mình áp dụng design system này vào project của bạn.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dilvgt265q5d_1","name":"stitch__list_design_systems","arguments":{"projectId":"13261989784115652519"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":3073,"output":389,"cacheRead":68001,"cacheWrite":415,"totalTokens":