{"type":"message","id":"622dd87a","parentId":"3bab45bf","timestamp":"2026-04-12T06:01:45.551Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that the `designSystem` parameter is being passed as a JSON string instead of an object. I need to pass it as a proper JSON object. Let me construct the call properly.\n\nLooking at the schema, the `designSystem` parameter should be an object that conforms to the DesignSystem type. The tool schema says:\n```\n\"designSystem\": {\"$ref\": \"#/$defs/DesignSystem\"}\n```\n\nSo I need to pass the designSystem as a JSON object, not as a string. The issue might be that the tool is receiving it as a string. Let me try passing it directly as a proper JSON object without stringifying it.\n\nWait, actually looking at the error message more carefully: \"designSystem: must be object\" - it seems the tool is receiving the value but it's not a valid DesignSystem object. \n\nThe tool received it as a string because I wrote it in JSON string format in the tool call. I need to pass it as a proper JSON object with the correct DesignSystem schema structure instead. The DesignSystem type requires a theme object with colorMode, font, and other properties, so I should structure it accordingly rather than passing it as a string representation.","thinkingSignature":"e84c8b595399aff3a4d74a752049b22f5775893fe758e967836ccda595b3dd0f"},{"type":"text","text":"The design system parameter needs to be a raw JSON object. Let me retry with the correct structure.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jjxsgs4zwphw_1","name":"stitch__create_design_system","arguments":{"designSystem":"{\"displayName\": \"Aethelgard Noir\", \"theme\": {\"colorMode\": \"LIGHT\", \"font\": \"NOTO_SERIF\", \"customColor\": \"#000000\", \"headlineFont\": \"NOTO_SERIF\", \"bodyFont\": \"MANROPE\", \"labelFont\": \"MANROPE\", \"namedColors\": {\"background\": \"#f9f9f9\", \"error\": \"#9e3f4e\", \"error_container\": \"#ff8b9a\", \"error_dim\": \