{"type":"message","id":"72ce5917","parentId":"200ecff5","timestamp":"2026-04-12T06:01:55.464Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The tool is still receiving the `designSystem` as a string. The issue is that I'm writing the JSON object as a string in the tool call. The tool's JSON schema requires `designSystem` to be an object, but the OpenClaw tool call is parsing it as a string.\n\nLet me look at this differently. The schema for `stitch__create_design_system` says:\n```\n\"designSystem\": {\"$ref\": \"#/$defs/DesignSystem\"}\n```\n\nBut the actual parameter in the tool call needs to be a JSON object. The issue is that when I pass a complex nested JSON object in the XML tool call format, it might be getting serialized as a string.\n \nLooking at the error message more closely, it's showing the value as a string with escaped quotes, which confirms the tool is receiving it as a string rather than a parsed object. I'm realizing the issue might be with how I'm structuring the parameter in the tool call itself.\n\nThe real problem could be that the DesignSystem schema has stricter requirements than what I'm providing, or the MCP server doesn't support certain fields. I should try a simpler approach—just create the design system with minimal required fields and let Stitch fill in the rest, or maybe skip the create step entirely and apply the reference design system directly to our generated screens using the assets endpoint.","thinkingSignature":"6876b6f97d0af3b418a5f14d12591dc3a4e6a4e03d0f084af8996594d6dcdfb5"},{"type":"text","text":"Let me try the correct approach — apply the reference design system directly to our project screens.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_yoas2vwzt1g4_1","name":"stitch__apply_design_system","arguments":{"assetId":"40e982ef8dfb4af2ab0af498ef8cfff6","projectId":"12108154905534221530","selectedScreenInstances":[]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":