{"type":"message","id":"a363f9bc","parentId":"811abf6a","timestamp":"2026-04-12T06:25:09.057Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see the reference project has 6 screens already generated:\n1. Home - The Curator (10048px height, full scroll)\n2. Collection - The Edit\n3. Shopping Bag\n4. My Account - The Curator\n5. Checkout - Secure Payment\n6. Product Detail - Essential Silk Coat\n\nThese are all DESKTOP screens. The user wants MOBILE screens. Let me check if the user's project has permission issues.\n\nThe key insight is: the reference project (13261989784115652519) has screens but my project (12108154905534221530) doesn't. And there's a permission issue.\n \nThe reference project is private and I'm listed as the owner, but I'm getting \"caller does not have permission\" when trying to list screens from my own project. The project ID I'm using is the numeric string 12108154905534221530, which should be correct, so this might be a user role or permissions configuration issue within the Stitch system itself. Let me try adjusting how I'm passing the project ID to the API.\n\nActually, I'm seeing that the reference project uses a different ID format starting with \"projects/\" while mine is just the raw number. Both seem to work as input parameters, but they're different identifier formats. The error suggests the MCP server itself doesn't have permission to access my project, even though I'm listed as the owner—which points to a Google Cloud identity or OAuth scope problem rather than a project configuration issue.\n\nLooking at the screenshot metadata, the reference project has 6 desktop screens already, while my project has no screens due to the permission error. The user picked a design they liked from my project, so maybe the solution is to work with what's already generated in the reference project rather than trying to create new screens from scratch. I could offer the user two options: export those 6 designs as HTML/CSS code and apply the \"Aethelgard Noir\" design system from them, or try using the reference project ID directly for generation. But actually, the Stitch MCP might just need a project ID format that includes the \"projects/\" prefix, so let me try that approach with the generate_screen_from_text tool. I need to reconsider this approach—the user selected a design from the reference project, and since Stitch MCP won't work with our project ID, I should pivot to a more practical solution: use the senior-frontend agent to implement the design based on the screenshots and design system documentation, which would be more effective than continuing to troubleshoot the Stitch integration.","thinkingSignature":"c82740a16ad84d5bf50f6cc418ab24761f322e42f9261d4dc1081d0910ef7e42"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] 📊 **Pipeline Status — Stitch bị chặn cứng**\n\nTin tốt: Reference project bạn chọn **đã có 6 screens** chất lượng cao:\n\n| Screen | Title |\n|--------|-------|\n| 1 | Home - The Curator |\n| 2 | Collection - The Edit |\n| 3 | Shopping Bag |\n| 4 | My Account - The Curator |\n| 5 | Checkout - Secure Payment |\n| 6 | Product Detail - Essential Silk Coat |\n\n**Vấn đề:** Project `12108154905534221530` (của mình) bị Stitch từ chối quyền truy cập — không tạo được screen mới.\n\n**2 hướng đi:**\n\n**A) Dùng reference project làm source** — export 6 screens hiện có → chuyển sang `senior-frontend` build mobile UI từ design specs\n**B) Tạo project Stitch mới** — tạo fresh project, apply design system, generate mobile screens\n\nBạn chọn hướng nào?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":5664,"output":767,"cacheRead":76471,"cacheWrite":472,"totalTokens":83374,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775975088803,"responseId":"062a6db235caec75edc513191d81eb0d"}}
