{"type":"message","id":"ec37bd60","parentId":"2ec46b78","timestamp":"2026-04-12T07:32:38.043Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to connect to their Confluence space \"ahv works\" using MCP and read the requirements. I need to check if there's a Confluence MCP tool available, or if I need to configure one. Let me check what MCP tools are available and see if there's a Confluence integration.\n\nLooking at the available tools, I don't see a Confluence MCP tool listed. I should check if there's a Confluence MCP configured or if I need to set one up.\n\nActually, looking at the context - the user is talking about connecting to a Confluence space. I should check if there's a Confluence MCP server configured. Let me check the MCP configuration.","thinkingSignature":"eb83135bbd11c6a4c8dec7fd98208c10c155f87a202f7cc9dab6d78ee63da3e8"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_w9kzk82j239a_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); mcp=d.get('mcp',{}); print(json.dumps(mcp, indent=2))\" 2>/dev/null || echo \"No MCP config found in openclaw.json\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":230,"output":227,"cacheRead":8153,"cacheWrite":82326,"totalTokens":90936,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775979146503,"responseId":"062a7d8b31eb46640d806f524a39f06a"}}
