{"type":"message","id":"a52937bb","parentId":"8348cddc","timestamp":"2026-04-12T07:32:48.617Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The MCP config only has Stitch. There's no Confluence MCP server configured. I need to set up a Confluence MCP. \n\nI can use the Confluence MCP server from the open source community. The most common one is from atlassian themselves or from MCP marketplace. Let me check what's available.\n\nActually, I should ask the user for their Confluence credentials or API token so I can set up the MCP. Or I could try to access Confluence via web_fetch.\n\nLet me try web_fetch first to see if I can access the Confluence page, and also check if there's a Confluence MCP available.\n\nActually, the cleanest approach would be to:\n\n\n1. Ask the user for their Confluence domain/URL and API token\n2. Set up the Confluence MCP server\n3. Then read the space\n\nLet me ask the user for the Confluence details.","thinkingSignature":"92660446ac1ffc50b78e4d339394820e5e03c360901fe009a7d5ee996b1323e2"},{"type":"text","text":"\nHiện tại MCP chỉ có Stitch. Chưa có Confluence MCP. Cần setup thêm.\n\n**Mình cần từ bạn:**\n1. Confluence domain (VD: `ahv.atlassian.net` hoặc `yourcompany.atlassian.net/wiki`)\n2. API token (lấy từ https://id.atlassian.com/manage-profile/security/api-tokens)\n\n**Cách nhanh nhất:** Nếu bạn có URL trang Confluence cụ thể, gửi mình link — mình dùng `web_fetch` đọc trực tiếp trước, không cần MCP.\n\nBạn muốn dùng cách nào?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":173,"output":349,"cacheRead":90395,"cacheWrite":477,"totalTokens":91394,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775979158188,"responseId":"062a7d97a1cd84ee600c810f9c35a869"}}
