{"type":"message","id":"eab4d7b1","parentId":"a240ac55","timestamp":"2026-04-12T07:34:14.911Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Confluence MCP is configured in `mcpServers`. The gateway needs to be restarted for it to take effect. But the user said they already restarted the gateway. Maybe it just needs time to load, or maybe the gateway restart didn't pick up the new config.\n\nLet me check if the confluence MCP tools are now available. Actually, I should test if the tools are available now. The `mcpServers` section might be the new way to configure MCP servers in OpenClaw v4. Let me try to check if the confluence tools are accessible.\n\nActually, looking at the tool list available to me, I don't see any confluence-specific tools. The tools I have are: read, edit, write, exec, process, cron, tts, agents_list, sessions_list, sessions_history, sessions_send, sessions_spawn, sessions_yield, subagents, session_status, memory_search, memory_get, web_search, web_fetch, image, stitch__*, browser.\n\n\nThe user might need to restart the gateway again since the new MCP server hasn't loaded yet, or I should just try using web_fetch directly with the Confluence URL to see if that works.","thinkingSignature":"09218e1a8c95dd7701c46fd677be7baf53260c18e8da969c8b4e686fa1602d41"},{"type":"text","text":"Có rồi — Confluence MCP đã được config trong `mcpServers`. Thử đọc Confluence space ngay.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_p7rjuti98nk8_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"npx -y confluence-mcp-server --help 2>&1 | head -5 || echo \"trying direct call\"","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":304,"output":325,"cacheRead":91743,"cacheWrite":280,"totalTokens":92652,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775979245445,"responseId":"062a7dee3808fe1c35138498142a099b"}}
