{"type":"message","id":"a699815e","parentId":"e38bca7d","timestamp":"2026-04-12T07:34:45.129Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The web fetch redirected to a login page - it requires authentication. The Confluence MCP is the right way to access it since it has the API token configured.\n\nLet me check if the confluence MCP tools are actually available now. I don't see any confluence-specific tools in my tool list. The MCP server might need a gateway restart or might not be loaded yet.\n\nLet me try to check if there's a confluence tool available by trying to use it directly. Actually, I should try a different approach - let me check if the confluence MCP tools are available by looking at what tools are accessible to me.\n\nLooking at my available tools, I don't see any confluence-specific MCP tools. The tools I have are:\n\n\n- read, edit, write, exec, process, cron, tts, agents_list, sessions_list, sessions_history, sessions_send, sessions_spawn, sessions_yield, subagents, session_status, memory_search, memory_get, web_search, web_fetch, image, stitch__*, browser\n\nThe confluence MCP server hasn't loaded yet even though the gateway was restarted. The issue might be that `mcpServers` is a new field in OpenClaw v4 and the gateway doesn't support it in the current version.\n\nLet me try using the Confluence REST API directly with the credentials from the config - username `ninhkhuongpl7@gmail.com` and the API token - to fetch the space details and pages.","thinkingSignature":"e3cd4f8a0df011bf5bbcbdf750d1f97f6c1d03241a56b4294661729277ff487c"},{"type":"text","text":"Web fetch bị redirect login. Thử gọi Confluence REST API trực tiếp với credentials từ config.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_v35it3u9gjta_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -u \"ninhkhuongpl7@gmail.com:ATATT3xFfGF0Xl6QZ-9lDBTiDym6FNGm1r6FJMt3u4ffIR8MjNDzl2oiKrRic_bdgOiIMWetDPY9FYMC_NPZ6O5uQVhiPip7oy2FlVGFqz5e214BGkaRoKmHz2XauaQG0A7rRq-7Lp8jp79