{"type":"message","id":"dcbb4d0a","parentId":"65a82d57","timestamp":"2026-04-12T07:35:46.446Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The API is returning 403 Forbidden when fetching individual pages, even though the space listing worked. This is strange. Let me check if maybe the space listing was cached or public, but individual pages need additional permissions. \n\nActually, let me try with a different approach - maybe using the Confluence Cloud REST API with the proper authentication header. The issue might be that `urllib` doesn't properly handle the HTTP Basic Auth. Let me try with requests or curl.\n\nActually, wait - the space listing worked with curl using `-u` flag for basic auth. But individual page fetches are getting 403. Let me try curl directly.","thinkingSignature":"608b800b3cff262210e25fb1e45dc35f7f53529544c49eadf9a4e14e2718c59f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_a749f8li6pep_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"TOKEN=\"ATATT3xFfGF0Xl6QZ-9lDBTiDym6FNGm1r6FJMt3u4ffIR8MjNDzl2oiKrRic_bdgOiIMWetDPY9FYMC_NPZ6O5uQVhiPip7oy2FlVGFqz5e214BGkaRoKmHz2XauaQG0A7rRq-7Lp8jp79Rdct2H61IouXCLFY4vQyXP9T9BPJT7ysxfnzJv7g=F3088272\"\nUSER=\"ninhkhuongpl7@gmail.com\"\n\ncurl -s -u \"$USER:$TOKEN\" \\\n  \"https://dtlx.atlassian.net/wiki/rest/api/content/95092893?expand=body.storage,version\" \\\n  -H \"Accept: application/json\" | python3 -c \"\nimport json,sys,re,html\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\ntitle=d.get('title','')\nbody=d.get('body',{}).get('storage',{}).get('value','')\nbody=re.sub(r'<[^>]+>',' ',body)\nbody=re.sub(r'\\s+',' ',body).strip()\nbody=html.unescape(body)\nprint(f'Title: {title}')\nprint(body[:3000])\n\" 2>/dev/null","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":261,"output":455,"cacheRead":95730,"cacheWrite":1468,"totalTokens":97914,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775979337288,