{"type":"message","id":"976ab4e6","parentId":"8edd0cdc","timestamp":"2026-04-12T08:14:13.240Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to do a full code review of the AHV Works system with a report. This is a massive task - full backend + frontend review. Let me orchestrate this properly.\n\nBased on the SOUL.md rules, I need to:\n1. Use prompt-optimizer first\n2. Define memory-based handovers\n3. Trigger the appropriate agents\n4. Generate HANDOVER.md between agents\n5. Produce a final RELEASE.md\n\nThe scope is huge:\n- Backend: 38 modules, 55+ endpoints\n- Frontend: 18 modules\n\nI should spawn multiple agents in parallel to cover different aspects. Let me plan:\n\n\nI'll spin up `senior-backend`, `code-reviewer`, `security-reviewer`, and `database-reviewer` to tackle the backend in parallel, while `senior-frontend` handles the frontend. Each agent will document their findings in separate review files, and I'll write a coordination brief to the reviews directory to track the overall progress. Then I'll write a MEMO.md to the orchestrator workspace explaining the full review plan, spawn all the agents with clear instructions, and wait for them to complete before assembling the final RELEASE.md.","thinkingSignature":"9607fb5c8b679f78e86a843c602fbd143384585cb36d7355c9320ddfe63224af"},{"type":"text","text":"Rõ rồi — review toàn bộ AHV Works với báo cáo. Bắt đầu orchestration pipeline ngay.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xymbfe9ukk1j_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/reviews/MEMO.md","content":"# AHV Works — Full System Code Review\n\n**Project:** AHV HRM (ahv-works/ahv-hrm)\n**GitLab:** gitlab.com/ahv-works/ahv-hrm\n**Backend:** BE #78077025 | **Frontend:** FE #78077037\n**Scope:** Full system review — backend (38 modules) + frontend (18 modules)\n**Status:** IN PROGRESS\n**Started:** 2026-04-12\n\n## Review Agents (parallel)\n\n| Agent | Scope | Output file |\n|-------|-------|-------------|\n| senior-backend | BE architecture, 3-layer, API logic, controller/service/repo | backend-arch.md |\n| code-reviewer | BE + FE code quality, patterns, error handling | code-quality.md |\n| security-reviewer | Auth, permissions, OWASP, input validation | security.md |\n| database-reviewer | BE MongoDB schemas, indexes, query performance | database.md |\n| performance-optimizer | N+1 queries, slow endpoints, memory, indexing | performance.md |\n| senior-frontend | FE structure, components, Redux, routing, UX | frontend.md |\n\n## Pipeline\n1. prompt-optimizer (done — this memo)\n2. Agents spawn in parallel\n3. Each writes to reviews/ directory\n4. master-orchestrator compiles RELEASE.md\n\n## GitLab MCP Config\nToken: glpat-c_N4qQVxbcktRro-S5rdwGM6MQpvOjEKdTpoZDBsYg8.01.170axqn65\nBE ID: 78077025 | FE ID: 78077037\nAPI: https://gitlab.com/api/v4\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":263,"output":677,"cacheRead":117024,"cacheWrite":981,"totalTokens":118945,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775981636869,"responseId":"062a87470186a8a163a170909f487a21"}}
