{"type":"message","id":"07e8b33a","parentId":"22dc136b","timestamp":"2026-04-12T08:14:25.817Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, MEMO written. Now spawn the review agents in parallel. I'll spawn 4-5 agents simultaneously covering different aspects. I need to give each agent clear instructions about:\n1. Using GitLab MCP to read files\n2. Writing to the reviews/ directory\n3. Their specific scope\n\nLet me spawn:\n1. senior-backend → backend architecture review\n2. code-reviewer → full code quality\n3. security-reviewer → security audit\n4. database-reviewer → MongoDB schemas + indexes\n5. performance-optimizer → performance audit\n6. senior-frontend → frontend review\n\nI can spawn all in parallel since they're independent.\n\n\nNow I'll set up each agent with the GitLab API credentials and file paths they need to access and write to.","thinkingSignature":"7377a8bc8f0bb77e4c6429880b50d7b51e82c283d311dfa50a6e137f7bae835f"},{"type":"text","text":"Spawning 6 review agents song song.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_y6eri9bm25xr_1","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"Review the AHV Works backend architecture. Read all modules from GitLab (BE project ID: 78077025, token: glpat-c_N4qQVxbcktRro-S5rdwGM6MQpvOjEKdTpoZDBsYg8.01.170axqn65, API: https://gitlab.com/api/v4). Use GitLab MCP or curl commands to read files. Target modules: src/modules/* (all 38 modules). Evaluate: 1) 3-layer architecture (controller→service→repo), 2) API design quality, 3) validation patterns, 4) error handling, 5) code organization, 6) type safety, 7) missing modules vs Confluence spec. Write detailed findings to /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/reviews/backend-arch.md. Include: STRENGTHS, ISSUES (with severity: CRITICAL/HIGH/MEDIUM), RECOMMENDATIONS, and PRIORITY FIX LIST.","label":"ahv-works:review:backend","runtime":"subagent","agentId":"senior-backend","thinking":"medium","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/wor