{"type":"message","id":"ab68412e","parentId":"1b17117e","timestamp":"2026-04-12T08:29:31.162Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me write the security review.","thinkingSignature":"b92bb320cc35c1cdcd774a1f40a473dff65f58d00dc07b471126964e8b3b7283"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gsnrhrcvszdk_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/reviews/security.md","content":"# 🔐 Security Review — AHV Works\n**Branch:** `develop` (SHA: bfdf0515)  \n**Source:** `ahv-works/ahv-hrm/ahv-hrm-backend` (GitLab #78077025)  \n**Swagger API:** `develop` branch — 55+ endpoints reviewed  \n**Reviewed by:** Orbis — Security Reviewer (direct audit)\n\n---\n\n## ✅ STRENGTHS\n\n- **bcrypt with 10 salt rounds** — `hashPassword.ts` uses `bcrypt.hash(password, 10)` ✅\n- **`select: false` on password** — AccountSchema never returns password in queries ✅\n- **JWT with `tokenVersion`** — logout invalidation works by incrementing tokenVersion ✅\n- **JWT secret via env var** — `JWT_PRIVATE_KEY` not hardcoded ✅\n- **Permission-based RBAC** — `authorizationPermissionMiddleware` checks permissions against role permissions ✅\n- **Joi validation on all inputs** — every module has `*.validation.ts` with Joi schemas ✅\n- **Cookie + Bearer dual auth** — `credentials: true` in CORS + Bearer token ✅\n- **Socket.IO auth** — `authenticationSocket` validates token on socket handshake ✅\n- **API prefix `/api/v1`** — clean API versioning foundation ✅\n- **`trim()` middleware** — prevents leading/trailing whitespace injection ✅\n\n---\n\n## 🚨 CRITICAL VULNERABILITIES\n\n### C1. No Rate Limiting on Any Endpoint\n**Files:** `app.ts`, all route files\n\nEvery API endpoint is unprotected against brute force and DDoS. The login endpoint `/api/v1/auth/login` is especially vulnerable — an attacker can attempt unlimited password guesses.\n\n**Impact:** Account takeover via brute force on weak passwords.\n\n**Fix:** Add `express-rate-limit`:\n```ts\nimport rateLimit from 'express-rate-limit';\nconst authLimiter = rateLimit({\n  windowMs: 15 * 60 * 1000, // 15 min\n  max: 5,                   // 5 attempts per window\n  message: { success: false, message: 'Quá nhiều lần thử. Thử lại sau 15 phút.' }\n});\nrouter.post('/auth/login', authLimiter, login);\n```\nAlso apply a general API limiter (e.g., 100 req/min per IP) on all routes.\n\n### C2. Default Password \"123456\" on Employee Creation\n**File:** `src/modules/employees/employees.controller.ts`, `src/common/config/environment.ts`\n\n```ts\n// employees.controller.ts\nconst newAccount: IAccountPayload = {\n  password: ACCOUNT_DEFAULT_PASSWORD, // defaults to '123456'\n  ...\n};\n\n// environment.ts\nACCOUNT_DEFAULT_PASSWORD: string = process.env.ACCOUNT_DEFAULT_PASSWORD\n    ? process.env.ACCOUNT_DEFAULT_PASSWORD\n    : '123456';  // ⚠️ HARDCODED FALLBACK\n```\n\nEvery auto-created employee account starts with password `123456`. This is extremely dangerous if:\n- The HR admin creates accounts in bulk\n- An attacker has read access to the codebase (GitLab commit history)\n\n**Fix:** Enforce password change on first login. Generate a secure random temp password and force reset. Remove the hardcoded fallback.\n\n### C3. CORS Blocks All Origins in Production\n**File:** `src/app.ts`\n\n```ts\napp.use(cors({\n  origin: NODE_ENV === 'development' ? true : feURLs.length > 0 ? feURLs : false,\n  // ❌ In production: origin = false (blocks ALL cross-origin requests)\n  credentials: true,\n}));\n```\n\nIf `FE_SERVER` env is not set in production, `origin: false` blocks every request from the frontend, including legitimate ones from the deployed FE domain. Misconfiguration = total outage.\n\n**Fix:** Fail-fast if FE_SERVER is not set in production:\n```ts\nif (NODE_ENV === 'production' && feURLs.length === 0) {\n  throw new Error('FE_SERVER environment variable must be set in production');\n}\n```\n\n### C4. No Refresh Token — Sessions Die Silently\n**File:** `src/modules/auth/auth.controller.ts`\n\nOnly an access token is issued. No refresh token mechanism exists. When the access token expires, the user is logged out with no recovery path. This encourages long-lived tokens or users staying logged in indefinitely.\n\n**Impact:** Poor UX + encourages token theft (long-lived tokens = bigger attack window).\n\n**Fix:** Implement refresh token rotation with Redis storage:\n- Issue short-lived access token (15 min)\n- Issue long-lived refresh token (7 days) stored in HTTP-only cookie\n- On refresh: rotate refresh token, invalidate old one in Redis\n\n---\n\n## 🔴 HIGH RISKS\n\n### H1. Missing `ref` on accounts.employeeId\n**File:** `src/modules/accounts/accounts.model.ts`\n\n```ts\nemployeeId: { type: Types.ObjectId, trim: true }, // No ref!\n```\n\nMongoose won't enforce referential integrity. An invalid ObjectId could be stored, causing `populate()` failures or orphaned accounts.\n\n**Fix:** Add `ref: 'Employees'`.\n\n### H2. Missing Authorization Check in NikoOrders\n**File:** `src/modules/nikoOrders/nikoOrders.service.ts` (not reviewed directly)\n\nSocial features (gifts, stars, orders) are high-value targets for IDOR attacks. Must verify:\n- Employee can only see their own orders\n- Employee can only redeem their own stars\n- Stars can't go negative\n\n### H3. No Helmet.js Security Headers\n**File:** `src/app.ts`\n\nNo security headers are set:\n- No `X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff`\n- No `X-Frame-Options`\n- No `Content-Security-Policy`\n- No `Strict-Transport-Security` (HSTS)\n\n**Fix:** Add Helmet:\n```ts\nimport helmet from 'helmet';\napp.use(helmet());\n```\n\n### H4. Sensitive Data in JWT Payload\n**File:** `src/common/utils/token.ts`\n\n```ts\nconst data: ITokenPayload = {\n  accountId: payload.accountId,\n  roleName: payload.roleName,\n  tokenVersion: payload.tokenVersion,  // ⚠️ Included in token\n};\n```\n\n`tokenVersion` is a security-sensitive field included in the JWT. While this is acceptable, verify the token is signed with RS256 (asymmetric) rather than HS256 (symmetric) for production to prevent key compromise.\n\nCheck: Is `JWT_PRIVATE_KEY` an RSA private key or a simple secret string?\n\n### H5. Loose Password Validation (Only Min Length)\n**File:** `src/modules/accounts/accounts.validation.ts`\n\n```ts\npassword: Joi.string().min(6).required()\n```\n\nOnly checks `min(6)`. No:\n- Uppercase requirement\n- Number requirement  \n- Special character requirement\n- Maximum length check\n\nAn attacker who gets a password hash can crack a 6-character password in seconds.\n\n**Fix:**\n```ts\npassword: Joi.string()\n  .min(8).max(128)\n  .pattern(/^(?=.*[a-z])(?=.*[A-Z])(?=.*\\d)/)\n  .required()\n  .messages({ 'string.pattern.base': 'Mật khẩu phải chứa ít nhất 1 chữ hoa, 1 chữ thường và 1 số' })\n```\n\n### H6. Multer File Upload — No File Type Validation\n**File:** `src/common/routes/index.ts`\n\n```ts\nconst storage = multer.diskStorage({ destination: (req, file, cb) => cb(null, './uploads') });\nconst upload = multer({ storage });\n```\n\nNo `fileFilter` to restrict uploaded file types. An attacker can upload:\n- Executable scripts (`.php`, `.js`, `.sh`)\n- Malicious PDFs\n- SVG files with XSS payloads\n\n**Fix:**\n```ts\nconst upload = multer({\n  storage,\n  fileFilter: (req, file, cb) => {\n    const allowed = /jpeg|jpg|png|pdf|doc|docx/;\n    const ext = allowed.test(path.extname(file.originalname).toLowerCase());\n    const mime = allowed.test(file.mimetype);\n    if (ext && mime) return cb(null, true);\n    cb(new Error('Chỉ chấp nhận file hình ảnh và tài liệu'));\n  },\n  limits: { fileSize: 5 * 1024 * 1024 } // 5MB max\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n## 🟡 MEDIUM RISKS\n\n### M1. Auth Middleware N+1 on Every Request\n**File:** `src/common/middlewares/authen.middleware.ts`\n\nEvery authenticated request hits the DB 3 times:\n1. `accountService.getAccountById()` → DB\n2. `accountRole.getAccountRoleByAccountId()` → DB\n3. `roleService.getRoleById()` → DB\n\nNo caching. On a system with 1000 concurrent users, that's 3000 DB reads per request cycle.\n\n**Fix:** Cache user+role in Redis with short TTL (5 min). Invalidate on role change.\n\n### M2. SystemLogs Collects IP/UserAgent — Potential PII Issues\n**File:** `src/modules/systemLogs/systemLog.model.ts`\n\nStoring `ipAddress`, `userAgent`, `location` — may fall under GDPR/PĐVN data protection requirements. No consent mechanism.\n\n**Recommendation:** Add data retention policy, anonymization, and privacy notice.\n\n### M3. No Input Sanitization for XSS\n**Files:** All `*.validation.ts`\n\nJoi validates data types and formats but does NOT sanitize HTML. If any field (e.g., `description`, `reason`, `note`) is rendered on the frontend without escaping, XSS is possible.\n\n**Fix:** Add DOMPurify on the frontend before rendering rich text fields.\n\n### M4. Error Handler Leaks Stack Traces\n**File:** `src/common/middlewares/error.middleware.ts`\n\nIn development mode, Mongoose and Express may leak stack traces in API responses, revealing internal implementation details.\n\n**Fix:** Ensure `NODE_ENV === 'production'` completely strips error details from responses.\n\n### M5. No IDOR Protection on Entity Endpoints\nCheck each `getOne` endpoint pattern:\n```\nGET /api/v1/employees/:id\nGET /api/v1/leave-requests/:id\nGET /api/v1/contracts/:id\n```\n\nThe `verifyAdminOrOwner` middleware only covers `/employees/:id`. Most other entities (leaveRequests, contracts, payroll) have no ownership check — any authenticated user can access any other user's records by guessing the ID.\n\n**Fix:** Add resource ownership checks to all sensitive entity endpoints.\n\n---\n\n## 📋 RECOMMENDATIONS\n\n### Immediate (Before Go-Live)\n1. Add `express-rate-limit` — protect auth and general API\n2. Remove hardcoded `123456` default password; force password reset on first login\n3. Fail-fast on missing `FE_SERVER` in production CORS config\n4. Implement refresh token rotation\n5. Add Helmet.js security headers\n6. Add file type validation to Multer uploads\n7. Add unique indexes to Employees (email, code, phone) — prevents duplicate accounts\n\n### Before Production Scale\n8. Move JWT to RS256 (asymmetric) if not already\n9. Cache auth middleware results in Redis\n10. Add IDOR checks on all entity endpoints\n11. Audit all file upload paths for path traversal\n12. Add `X-Request-ID` header for request tracing\n13. Set up CSP headers (Content-Security-Policy)\n\n### Ongoing\n14. Run OWASP ZAP or Burp Suite scan monthly\n15. Set up Snyk/Dependabot for dependency vulnerability alerts\n16. Add audit log for permission/role changes (currently not tracked in systemLogs)\n\n---\n\n## 🔧 PRIORITY FIX LIST\n\n| # | Priority | Fix | Attack Vector | Effort |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 | 🔴 P0 | Rate limiting on /auth/login (5 attempts/15min) | Brute force | Low |\n| 2 | 🔴 P0 | Remove hardcoded '123456' default password | Account takeover | Low |\n| 3 | 🔴 P0 | Fix CORS origin=false in production | Complete outage | Low |\n| 4 | 🔴 P0 | Add refresh token rotation | Session expiry UX + security | Medium |\n| 5 | 🟠 P1 | Add Helmet.js security headers | XSS, clickjacking, MIME sniffing | Low |\n| 6 | 🟠 P1 | File type validation in Multer | Malicious file upload | Low |\n| 7 | 🟠 P1 | Unique indexes on Employees | Account duplicate/collision | Low |\n| 8 | 🟠 P1 | IDOR checks on entity endpoints | Unauthorized data access | Medium |\n| 9 | 🟡 P2 | Cache auth middleware in Redis | Performance + DB load | Medium |\n| 10 | 🟡 P2 | Strengthen password validation (Joi) | Weak password cracking | Low |\n| 11 | 🟡 P2 | Add CSP headers | XSS | Medium |\n| 12 | 🟡 P2 | XSS sanitization on rich text fields | Stored XSS | Medium |\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":121,"output":2902,"cacheRead":52035,"cacheWrite":3246,"totalTokens":58304,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775982515747,"responseId":"062a8ab5e4d219a6ab26ad18cb10ce0a"}}
