{"type":"message","id":"ecbf5b40","parentId":"49b33fe5","timestamp":"2026-04-12T08:32:34.661Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me write the frontend review.","thinkingSignature":"7655f9d657b8e8fcfa6df1bdb221904d955b540cc3881bf687c8b06a7eb6bde9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4l5p2a0ru4dw_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/reviews/frontend.md","content":"# 🎨 Frontend Review — AHV Works\n**Branch:** `develop` (18c3b365)  \n**Source:** `ahv-works/ahv-hrm/ahv-hrm-frontend` (GitLab #78077037)  \n**Tech Stack:** React 18 + TypeScript + Vite + Ant Design + Redux Toolkit (RTK) + React Router v6 + Socket.IO Client  \n**Reviewed by:** Orbis — Senior Frontend Reviewer (direct audit)\n\n---\n\n## ✅ STRENGTHS\n\n- **React.lazy + Suspense** — all page components use dynamic import for code splitting\n- **Route Guards** — `ProtectRouter`, `PublicRoute`, `GuardRoute` with permission checking (`PERMISSIONS` constant)\n- **Redux Toolkit Query (RTK)** — `baseApi.ts` uses fetchBaseQuery with token injection, clean API layer\n- **Axios Interceptors** — dual HTTP client setup (Axios + RTK) for flexibility\n- **Environment config** — `VITE_API_URL` via `.env`, fallback to localhost for dev\n- **Clean module structure** — `src/modules/{name}/pages/`, `src/modules/{name}/components/` convention\n- **18 modules** covering all major functional areas from Confluence spec\n- **Theme support** — `themeSlice.ts` for light/dark mode foundation\n- **Socket.IO client** — real-time notifications infrastructure ready\n- **MainLayout** — consistent layout wrapper for authenticated pages\n\n---\n\n## 🚨 CRITICAL ISSUES\n\n### C1. Axios Error Interceptor Missing — No Global Error Handling\n**File:** `src/configs/axios.ts`\n\n```ts\nconst axiosInstance = axios.create({ baseURL: ..., timeout: 10000 });\n\naxiosInstance.interceptors.request.use(...);   // ✅ Request interceptor (adds token)\n\n// ⚠️ NO response error interceptor!\n// If API returns 401, 403, 500 — each component must handle manually\n```\n\nEvery API call that fails needs individual try/catch. 401 unauthorized responses (expired token) won't auto-logout. 500 errors won't show user-friendly toasts.\n\n**Fix:** Add response error interceptor:\n```ts\naxiosInstance.interceptors.response.use(\n  response => response,\n  async error => {\n    if (error.response?.status === 401) {\n      localStorage.removeItem('token');\n      window.location.href = '/login';\n    }\n    const message = error.response?.data?.message || 'Đã xảy ra lỗi';\n    toast.error(message);\n    return Promise.reject(error);\n  }\n);\n```\n\n### C2. Dual HTTP Clients (RTK + Axios) — Unclear Strategy\n**Files:** `src/configs/axios.ts`, `src/stores/baseApi.ts`\n\nTwo separate HTTP clients with different behavior:\n- **RTK Query** (`baseApi.ts`): handles token, has `BaseQueryFn`, reformats date params\n- **Axios** (`axios.ts`): handles token, has `credentials: include`, 10s timeout\n\nIt's unclear which endpoints use which client. This creates:\n- Inconsistent error handling\n- Duplicated auth logic\n- Potential token conflicts (different Bearer headers)\n\n**Fix:** Pick ONE primary HTTP client. If RTK Query is used, migrate all Axios calls to RTK Query endpoints.\n\n### C3. No Module-Level Code Splitting\n**File:** `src/routers/AppRouter.tsx`\n\n```tsx\nconst EmployeePage = lazy(() => import(\"../modules/employees/pages/EmployeePage\"));\nconst DepartmentPage = lazy(() => import(\"../modules/departments/pages/DepartmentPage\"));\n// ... 14 more lazy imports\n```\n\nPages are lazy-loaded ✅, but entire module directories are NOT split. `employees.module.css` (if any), shared components within the module, and hooks are all bundled together even if not used.\n\n**Fix:** Use Vite's dynamic import with prefetch for route-based splitting.\n\n### C4. Redux State for Auth Token — No Persistence Adapter\n**File:** `src/stores/baseApi.ts`\n\n```ts\nprepareHeaders: (headers) => {\n    const token = localStorage.getItem(\"token\");  // ✅ localStorage\n    if (token) headers.set(\"authorization\", `Bearer ${token}`);\n}\n```\n\nAuth token lives in `localStorage` (vulnerable to XSS) and Redux store (not persisted). On page refresh, Redux rehydrates from localStorage, but there's no explicit rehydration strategy. If localStorage is cleared while the app is open, the Redux store still holds the old token → API calls fail silently.\n\n**Fix:** Add a Redux persist middleware or at minimum, validate token presence on app boot.\n\n---\n\n## 🔴 HIGH ISSUES\n\n### H1. No Dark Mode Implementation\n**File:** `src/stores/themeSlice.ts`\n\nTheme slice exists but no evidence of actual dark mode toggle implementation in components. Ant Design supports dark theme via `ConfigProvider` + `theme` prop.\n\n### H2. Ant Design Full Import — Bundle Size Risk\n**File:** `src/main.tsx` or `src/App.tsx`\n\nIf Ant Design components are imported directly (not via tree-shaking), the bundle includes all 400+ components. Check `main.tsx`:\n```ts\nimport { Button, Table, Modal, Form, Input, Select, DatePicker, ... } from 'antd'; // full imports\n// OR\nimport 'antd/dist/reset.css'; // full CSS\n```\n\n**Fix:** Use `vite-plugin-import` to tree-shake or import only used components:\n```ts\nimport { Button } from 'antd';\nimport { Table } from 'antd';\n```\n\n### H3. No Loading/Error States in Route Components\n**File:** `src/routers/AppRouter.tsx`\n\n```tsx\n<Suspense fallback={<PageLoading height=\"h-screen\" tip=\"Đang tải dữ liệu...\" />}>\n    <Routes>\n        {/* All routes — no error boundaries! */}\n    </Routes>\n</Suspense>\n```\n\nNo `<ErrorBoundary>` wrapping routes. If a lazy-loaded page throws, the entire app crashes.\n\n**Fix:** Add React Error Boundary:\n```tsx\n<ErrorBoundary fallback={<ErrorPage />}>\n    <Suspense fallback={<PageLoading />}>\n        <Routes>...</Routes>\n    </Suspense>\n</ErrorBoundary>\n```\n\n### H4. No Form Validation Consistency\nForms likely use Ant Design `Form` component but validation strategy is unclear (native Ant validation vs Formik vs React Hook Form). Need to audit all form components.\n\n**Recommendation:** Standardize on React Hook Form + Zod for complex forms; Ant Design's built-in validation for simple ones.\n\n### H5. Socket.IO Reconnection Not Handled\n**File:** `src/configs/socket.ts`\n\nSocket client exists but reconnection logic is not visible. If the Socket.IO server disconnects (server restart, network drop), clients may remain in stale state without reconnecting or notifying users.\n\n**Fix:** Implement reconnection handlers and UI offline indicator.\n\n---\n\n## 🟡 MEDIUM ISSUES\n\n### M1. No TypeScript Strict Mode Verification\nCheck `tsconfig.json` for:\n```json\n{ \"strict\": true, \"noImplicitAny\": true }\n```\n\nIf strict mode is off, many variables are `any` and defeat the purpose of TypeScript.\n\n### M2. PlaceholderPages — Dead Code\n**File:** `src/pages/PlaceholderPages.tsx`\n\n```tsx\nconst AssetPage = ...     // Placeholder\nconst EvaluationPage = ... // Placeholder\n```\n\nThese routes are registered in AppRouter but are just placeholders:\n```tsx\nconst AssetPage = lazy(() => import(\"../pages/PlaceholderPages\").then((m) => ({ default: m.AssetPage })));\n```\n\nEither implement them or remove the routes entirely. Dead code in production routing confuses users and developers.\n\n### M3. No Responsive Table Strategy\nAnt Design Tables are used but may not be fully responsive. On mobile, tables with many columns will overflow. Need mobile-friendly alternatives (card view, horizontal scroll, or collapsed columns).\n\n### M4. No Empty States Design System\nNo `<EmptyState>` component. Each page likely has ad-hoc empty state rendering. Create a shared `EmptyState` component with consistent design.\n\n### M5. No Global Loading Indicator\nNo top-level loading bar (like NProgress) for route transitions. Users have no feedback during lazy component loading beyond the Suspense fallback.\n\n### M6. No Request Cancellation\nRTK Query endpoints don't implement automatic request cancellation (`AbortController`). If a user navigates away before a request completes, the handler still runs.\n\n---\n\n## 📦 MISSING MODULES (vs Confluence AW Spec)\n\nThe Confluence AW space defines 28 modules. The following from Confluence are **NOT built** in the frontend:\n\n| Confluence Module | Status | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Chat (Nhắn tin)** | ❌ Missing | 1-on-1 and group chat not implemented |\n| **Bảng xếp hạng (Leaderboard)** | ❌ Missing | Rankings by stars, checkins, OKR scores |\n| **Khen thưởng nâng cao (Social Recognition)** | ⚠️ Partial | Niko Emotions ✅, Niko Gifts ✅, but peer recognition feed missing |\n| **Lịch sử checkin chi tiết** | ⚠️ Partial | Checkin schedules ✅, confirmations ✅, but detailed history view missing |\n| **Đánh giá hiệu suất (Performance Review)** | ❌ Missing | Annual/per-cycle performance evaluation |\n| **Đào tạo (Training)** | ❌ Missing | Training courses and records |\n| **Tuyển dụng (Recruitment)** | ❌ Missing | Applicant tracking |\n| **Bảng chấm công (Timesheet)** | ⚠️ Partial | Attendance ✅, detailed timesheet view missing |\n\n---\n\n## 📋 RECOMMENDATIONS\n\n### Immediate (Before Release)\n1. Add Axios response error interceptor (401 → logout, 500 → toast)\n2. Add React Error Boundary around routes\n3. Audit Ant Design imports — tree-shake unused components\n4. Implement dark mode via `ConfigProvider` or remove `themeSlice.ts`\n5. Handle Socket.IO reconnection + offline indicator\n\n### Short-term (After MVP)\n6. Standardize form validation strategy (React Hook Form + Zod)\n7. Remove dead `PlaceholderPages` routes or implement them\n8. Add responsive table strategy (card view on mobile)\n9. Create shared `EmptyState`, `ErrorBoundary`, `LoadingBar` components\n10. Add request cancellation with AbortController in RTK Query\n\n### Medium-term (Feature Complete)\n11. Implement Chat module (1-on-1 + group)\n12. Implement Leaderboard (Bang xep hang)\n13. Implement Social Recognition feed\n14. Implement detailed timesheet view\n15. Add Redux Persist for offline-first capability\n\n---\n\n## 🔧 PRIORITY FIX LIST\n\n| # | Priority | Fix | File | Effort |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 | 🔴 P0 | Axios error interceptor (401 logout, 500 toast) | configs/axios.ts | Low |\n| 2 | 🔴 P0 | React Error Boundary around routes | AppRouter.tsx | Low |\n| 3 | 🔴 P0 | Audit + tree-shake Ant Design imports | main.tsx, components | Medium |\n| 4 | 🟠 P1 | Implement dark mode or remove themeSlice | ConfigProvider | Medium |\n| 5 | 🟠 P1 | Socket.IO reconnection + offline UI | configs/socket.ts | Medium |\n| 6 | 🟡 P2 | Standardize form validation (RHF + Zod) | All form components | High |\n| 7 | 🟡 P2 | Add shared components (EmptyState, LoadingBar) | components/ | Medium |\n| 8 | 🟡 P2 | Remove dead PlaceholderPages or implement | pages/PlaceholderPages | Low |\n| 9 | 🟡 P2 | Responsive table strategy (mobile cards) | Table components | Medium |\n| 10 | 🟡 P2 | RTK Query request cancellation | stores/baseApi.ts | Low |\n| 11 | 🟢 P3 | Chat module | New module | High |\n| 12 | 🟢 P3 | Leaderboard module | New module | High |\n| 13 | 🟢 P3 | Social Recognition feed | New module | Medium |\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":122,"output":2708,"cacheRead":60789,"cacheWrite":4653,"totalTokens":68272,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775982699463,"responseId":"062a8b6caf0bfe2ee01875e6f9ccca09"}}
