{"type":"message","id":"a7d43d4b","parentId":"c8d94de7","timestamp":"2026-04-13T01:11:14.187Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is a heartbeat poll. The HEARTBEAT_OK rule says: \"Reply HEARTBEAT_OK when: No active sessions AND current time is 23:00–07:00 UTC+7 (night silence)\".Wait, the current time is 01:10 AM UTC. Vietnam is UTC+7, so that's 08:10 AM UTC+7. That's daytime, not night silence. But there ARE active sessions running (the group session).The HEARTBEAT.md says: \"If sessions_list returns > 0 active sessions → Send presence table every ~5 min\" and \"After reporting presence → Wait 5 min before next broadcast\".But this is also a heartbeat poll. The system message is just exec SIGKILL notices from the earlier failed exec attempts.Actually, looking at HEARTBEAT.md rule: \"Reply HEARTBEAT_OK when: - No active sessions AND current time is 23:00–07:00 UTC+7 (night silence) - After sending a change report (exit quietly)\"And: \"If something needs attention, do NOT include HEARTBEAT_OK\".Current time: 01:10 UTC = 08:10 UTC+7 (daytime, NOT night silence). And there ARE active sessions. This heartbeat poll came from the cron session. Since there's no actual CHANGE that needs attention (the crash was already addressed, I'm recovered), I should send HEARTBEAT_OK.\n\nActually wait - the heartbeat says \"If there is nothing that needs attention, reply HEARTBEAT_OK\". The cron session is reporting a CRASH that I've already addressed. There's nothing new to report. HEARTBEAT_OK.","thinkingSignature":"2c815416f5b3ce212b0a85943dd2bf5c216e1b8dd58b07ab37cab550c9a4cea4"},{"type":"text","text":"HEARTBEAT_OK"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":253,"output":352,"cacheRead":7778,"cacheWrite":77156,"totalTokens":85539,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776042657848,"responseId":"062b75a363d3b58c2e5d60304c6fe