{"type":"message","id":"26d4e5ed","parentId":"f2df60f5","timestamp":"2026-04-13T01:22:37.301Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This heartbeat is reporting the main orchestrator as crashed. But I'm active right now - I just responded to the previous heartbeat. The issue is that the cron session is seeing an old/different state. The \"main\" session 52c22b9d crashed, but I'm running on a different session (the telegram group session). The cron heartbeat is detecting the \"main\" session as crashed but doesn't know I'm alive on the group session.\n\nThis is just a stale heartbeat report - the system is actually healthy since I'm active. I should reply HEARTBEAT_OK.","thinkingSignature":"17fe09e7e560fc1a354361fc1cfb11a0911d146f703ae30181a5d523e30c59e1"},{"type":"text","text":"HEARTBEAT_OK\n\n*(Đã recovered — đang active trên telegram:group session. \"main\" crash là session cũ, không ảnh hưởng.)*"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":0,"output":161,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":85372,"totalTokens":85533,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776043347124,"responseId":"062b785484329175d1c758fc499b17e6"}}
